{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_25","type":"mcp_tool_call","server":"codex_apps","tool":"github_fetch_commit","arguments":{"repo_full_name":"BlueRay2/history-production","commit_sha":"83cba3d"},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"commit\": {\"sha\": \"83cba3d0209b5b8dbfceef50b85276df46e24e5e\", \"message\": \"task-02(kpi) MERGED: Codex r3 accepted + Gemini r2 accepted (r3 path-confusion)\\n\\nReview loop summary for task-02:\\n- r1 parallel Codex + Gemini: both request changes (union of 6 findings \\u2014\\n  OOB redirect deprecated, O_EXCL mismatch, test-coverage gap, env parser\\n  robustness, metrics validation, docstring claim).\\n- r1 union fix commit 290965a: all 6 findings addressed.\\n- r2 parallel: Codex request changes (1 MED \\u2014 rotate tmp cleanup); Gemini\\n  accepted (no comments).\\n- r2 fix commit d90fb3b: unique tmp name + try/except/finally + unlink on\\n  failure.\\n- r3 Codex accepted (no comments). Gemini r3 could not re-review due to\\n  path confusion (hallucinated repo path as 'claude-scripts' instead of\\n  'history-production'); no 429 capacity issue. Given Gemini r2 accepted\\n  the bundle and r3 delta is 15-line hygiene cleanup, merging with\\n  annotation 'gemini-r3-path-confusion' rather than strict gemini-degraded.\\n\\nReview: Codex-accepted r3; Gemini r2-accepted (bundle), r3 path-confusion\\n(no re-review of tmp-cleanup delta). Documented in\\nreviews/task-02/gemini-round-3.md coordinator disposition.\\n\\nBundle delivered:\\n- scripts/bootstrap_youtube_oauth.py (200 LOC, loopback OAuth + atomic write)\\n- ingest/youtube_client.py (175 LOC, typed fa\\u00e7ade)\\n- ingest/env_loader.py (62 LOC, robust parser)\\n- app/lib/retry.py (86 LOC, retry helper)\\n- 3 vcrpy cassettes (reference shapes)\\n- 41 tests passing (test_retry 5, test_migrations 9, test_bootstrap 7,\\n  test_env_loader 10, test_youtube_client 10)\\n- pyproject.toml: google-api-python-client + google-auth-oauthlib +\\n  google-auth (runtime); pytest + pytest-cov + pyyaml + vcrpy (dev)\\n\\nStatus: task-02 in-review (r 3) -> merged.\\n\\nNext: task-03 (append-snapshot ingest) + task-04 (history git parser)\\nboth depend only on task-02, now unblocked; task-04 not yet started\\nper \\u042f\\u0440\\u043e\\u0441\\u043b\\u0430\\u0432 focus directive (msg 6877) \\u2014 starting task-03 next.\\n\\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\", \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/BlueRay2/history-production/commits/83cba3d0209b5b8dbfceef50b85276df46e24e5e\", \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/BlueRay2/history-production/commit/83cba3d0209b5b8dbfceef50b85276df46e24e5e\", \"diff\": \"@@ -18,7 +18,7 @@ Full consensus artefacts (research, debates, findings register, verdicts) are in\\n | ID | File | Scope | Status | Codex review | Gemini review |\\n |---|---|---|---|---|---|\\n | 01 | [task-01-adr-and-schema.md](task-01-adr-and-schema.md) | Stack ADR (Flask+Jinja+HTMX+Chart.js+SQLite), DB schema, raw SQL migrations, `schema_migrations` table | `merged` | \\u2705 accepted r3 | \\u2705 accepted r1 |\\n-| 02 | [task-02-youtube-api-client.md](task-02-youtube-api-client.md) | OAuth install-flow, refresh-token cache in `/home/aiagent/.config/youtube-api/.env` (600), typed client wrapper, vcrpy cassette fixtures | `in-review (r 1)` | pending | pending |\\n+| 02 | [task-02-youtube-api-client.md](task-02-youtube-api-client.md) | OAuth install-flow, refresh-token cache in `/home/aiagent/.config/youtube-api/.env` (600), typed client wrapper, vcrpy cassette fixtures | `merged` | \\u2705 accepted r3 | \\u2705 accepted r2 (r3 path-confusion, no new delta review) |\\n | 03 | [task-03-append-snapshot-ingest.md](task-03-append-snapshot-ingest.md) | Ingestion runs table, rolling 45-d backfill, append-only writes with `observed_on`, preliminary-flag overwrite logic, first-run 45-d backfill script | `pending` | \\u2014 | \\u2014 |\\n | 04 | [task-04-history-git-parser.md](task-04-history-git-parser.md) | `ingest/history_git.py`, heuristic commit scoring (phase-\\\\d+ / script / final / lock patterns), confidence + evidence columns, golden git fixtures | `pending` | \\u2014 | \\u2014 |\\n | 05 | [task-05-mapping-and-derived-kpis.md](task-05-mapping-and-derived-kpis.md) | `video_project_map` + derived KPI views: cycle-time, scripts-per-week, script-iterations (approx), cost-per-video (fail-closed parser) | `pending` | \\u2014 | \\u2014 |\\n\\n@@ -0,0 +1,240 @@\\n+[health-check] gemini: ok\\n+\\n+\\n+\\n+\\n+\\n+\\n+\\n+\\n+\\n+\\n+\\n+\\n+{\\n+  config: {\\n+    url: 'https://cloudcode-pa.googleapis.com/v1internal:generateContent',\\n+    method: 'POST',\\n+    headers: {\\n+      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\\n+      'User-Agent': 'GeminiCLI/0.38.2/gemini-2.5-pro (linux; x64; terminal) google-api-nodejs-client/9.15.1',\\n+      Authorization: '<<REDACTED> - See `errorRedactor` option in `gaxios` for configuration>.',\\n+      'x-goog-api-client': 'gl-node/22.22.2',\\n+      Accept: 'application/json'\\n+    },\\n+    responseType: 'json',\\n+    body: `{\\\"model\\\":\\\"gemini-2.5-flash\\\",\\\"project\\\":\\\"continual-heuristic-wtd63\\\",\\\"user_prompt_id\\\":\\\"conseca-policy-enforcement\\\",\\\"request\\\":{\\\"contents\\\":[{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"parts\\\":[{\\\"text\\\":\\\"\\\\\\\\nYou are a security enforcement engine. Your goal is to check if a specific tool call complies with a given security policy.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nInput:\\\\\\\\n1.  **Security Policy:** A set of rules defining allowed and denied actions for this specific tool.\\\\\\\\n2.  **Tool Call:** The actual function call the system intends to execute.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSecurity Policy:\\\\\\\\n{\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\"permissions\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"allow\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\"constraints\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"Only allow reading the file 'scripts/bootstrap_youtube_oauth.py'. No other file paths are permitted.\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\"rationale\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"The user explicitly requested a review of changes in 'scripts/bootstrap_youtube_oauth.py' related to the specified commit. This allows local file inspection if the codebase is available.\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTool Call:\\\\\\\\n{\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"read_file\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\"args\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\"file_path\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"/home/aiagent/assistant/git/claude-scripts/scripts/bootstrap_youtube_oauth.py\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n  }\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nEvaluate the tool call against the policy.\\\\\\\\n1. Check if the tool is allowed.\\\\\\\\n2. Check if the arguments match the constraints.\\\\\\\\n3. Output a JSON object with:\\\\\\\\n   - \\\\\\\\\\\"decision\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"allow\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\"deny\\\\\\\\\\\", or \\\\\\\\\\\"ask_user\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\n   - \\\\\\\\\\\"reason\\\\\\\\\\\": A brief explanation.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nOutput strictly JSON.\\\\\\\\n\\\"}]}],\\\"generationConfig\\\":{\\\"responseMimeType\\\":\\\"application/json\\\",\\\"responseSchema\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"decision\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"enum\\\":[\\\"allow\\\",\\\"deny\\\",\\\"ask_user\\\"]},\\\"reason\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"decision\\\",\\\"reason\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false}},\\\"session_id\\\":\\\"15dcba69-262b-425e-b6a4-32b9e79978a5\\\"}}`,\\n+    retryConfig: {\\n+      retryDelay: 1000,\\n+      retry: 3,\\n+      noResponseRetries: 3,\\n+      statusCodesToRetry: [Array],\\n+      currentRetryAttempt: 0,\\n+      httpMethodsToRetry: [Array],\\n+      retryDelayMultiplier: 2,\\n+      timeOfFirstRequest: 1776804082899,\\n+      totalTimeout: 9007199254740991,\\n+      maxRetryDelay: 9007199254740991\\n+    },\\n+    paramsSerializer: [Function: paramsSerializer],\\n+    validateStatus: [Function: validateStatus],\\n+    errorRedactor: [Function: defaultErrorRe