d\\nper \\u042f\\u0440\\u043e\\u0441\\u043b\\u0430\\u0432 focus directive (msg 6877) \\u2014 starting task-03 next.\\n\\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\"}"}],"structured_content":{"commit":{"sha":"83cba3d0209b5b8dbfceef50b85276df46e24e5e","message":"task-02(kpi) MERGED: Codex r3 accepted + Gemini r2 accepted (r3 path-confusion)\n\nReview loop summary for task-02:\n- r1 parallel Codex + Gemini: both request changes (union of 6 findings —\n  OOB redirect deprecated, O_EXCL mismatch, test-coverage gap, env parser\n  robustness, metrics validation, docstring claim).\n- r1 union fix commit 290965a: all 6 findings addressed.\n- r2 parallel: Codex request changes (1 MED — rotate tmp cleanup); Gemini\n  accepted (no comments).\n- r2 fix commit d90fb3b: unique tmp name + try/except/finally + unlink on\n  failure.\n- r3 Codex accepted (no comments). Gemini r3 could not re-review due to\n  path confusion (hallucinated repo path as 'claude-scripts' instead of\n  'history-production'); no 429 capacity issue. Given Gemini r2 accepted\n  the bundle and r3 delta is 15-line hygiene cleanup, merging with\n  annotation 'gemini-r3-path-confusion' rather than strict gemini-degraded.\n\nReview: Codex-accepted r3; Gemini r2-accepted (bundle), r3 path-confusion\n(no re-review of tmp-cleanup delta). Documented in\nreviews/task-02/gemini-round-3.md coordinator disposition.\n\nBundle delivered:\n- scripts/bootstrap_youtube_oauth.py (200 LOC, loopback OAuth + atomic write)\n- ingest/youtube_client.py (175 LOC, typed façade)\n- ingest/env_loader.py (62 LOC, robust parser)\n- app/lib/retry.py (86 LOC, retry helper)\n- 3 vcrpy cassettes (reference shapes)\n- 41 tests passing (test_retry 5, test_migrations 9, test_bootstrap 7,\n  test_env_loader 10, test_youtube_client 10)\n- pyproject.toml: google-api-python-client + google-auth-oauthlib +\n  google-auth (runtime); pytest + pytest-cov + pyyaml + vcrpy (dev)\n\nStatus: task-02 in-review (r 3) -> merged.\n\nNex