{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_30","type":"mcp_tool_call","server":"codex_apps","tool":"github_fetch_commit","arguments":{"repo_full_name":"BlueRay2/history-production","commit_sha":"ca9b626"},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"commit\": {\"sha\": \"ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810\", \"message\": \"task-03(kpi): append-snapshot ingest + first-run backfill + 14 tests\\n\\nImplements task-03 per docs/tz/dashboard-kpi/task-03-append-snapshot-ingest.md.\\n\\n- app/repositories/metrics.py (140 LOC) \\u2014 SnapshotRow dataclass; write_snapshot_batch\\n  with INSERT OR IGNORE semantics inside BEGIN IMMEDIATE / COMMIT / ROLLBACK\\n  transaction; latest_snapshot with MAX(observed_on) via idx_*_metric_latest;\\n  count_snapshots ops helper. Append-only invariant documented: re-runs with\\n  fresh observed_on append new rows; same observed_on = no-op.\\n\\n- ingest/jobs.py (140 LOC) \\u2014 run_daily_refresh entry point. Target-date\\n  default = today-2 (YouTube 2-day lag). preliminary=True when observed\\n  <3 days after window_end. Weekly ISO-week windows computed from\\n  target_date. Opens ingestion_runs row with status='in_progress', closes\\n  with status in {ok, partial, api_failure, db_failure, quota_exhausted}.\\n  Exception classification: HttpError 429 \\u2192 quota_exhausted; other HttpError\\n  \\u2192 api_failure; sqlite3.Error \\u2192 db_failure. Accepts injected  +\\n   for test pinning.\\n\\n- ingest/first_run.py (60 LOC) \\u2014 one-shot 45-day backfill on empty DB.\\n  needs_first_run() checks channel_metric_snapshots row count below\\n  FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD=7. run_first_time_backfill iterates target dates from\\n  today-45 to today-2, aborts on quota_exhausted (partial progress preserved).\\n  CLI: python -m ingest.first_run.\\n\\n- tests/test_snapshot_append.py (6 tests): round-trip, same-observed-on\\n  no-op, fresh-observed-on append, video-vs-channel routing, FK enforcement\\n  on missing video, empty batch.\\n- tests/test_ingest_jobs.py (8 tests): happy path, preliminary flag boundary\\n  (<3 day vs older), ingestion_run record, HttpError 429 \\u2192 quota_exhausted\\n  status, empty analytics response = 0 rows, first_run skipped when populated,\\n  first_run fires on empty DB (44 daily calls for 44-day inclusive range),\\n  first_run aborts on quota mid-backfill.\\n\\nFull suite: 55 tests green (41 + 14).\\n\\nStatus: task-03 pending \\u2192 in-review (r 1). Dispatching PARALLEL Codex +\\nGemini review per process.md parallel model.\\n\\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\", \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/BlueRay2/history-production/commits/ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810\", \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/BlueRay2/history-production/commit/ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810\", \"diff\": \"\\n@@ -0,0 +1,158 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Metrics repository \\u2014 append-only snapshot reads and writes.\\n+\\n+Append-only invariant:\\n+  - Every snapshot row is identified by (entity, metric_key, grain, window,\\n+    observed_on). Re-pulls emit a NEW row with fresh `observed_on`.\\n+  - Dashboard reads select the latest row per (entity, metric_key, window)\\n+    via MAX(observed_on).\\n+  - Preliminary-flag handling: when YouTube's 2-day-lag window resettles\\n+    with stable values, caller may mark prior preliminary rows as stable by\\n+    writing a new row with preliminary=0; the legacy preliminary row stays\\n+    for audit.\\n+\\n+Consumed by: ingest/jobs.py (task-03 writer), dashboard views (task-06+).\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import sqlite3\\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\\n+from typing import Iterable\\n+\\n+\\n+@dataclass(frozen=True)\\n+class SnapshotRow:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Single append-only metric observation.\\n+\\n+    video_id == None marks a channel-level snapshot (stored in\\n+    channel_metric_snapshots). Otherwise the row lives in\\n+    video_metric_snapshots.\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+    metric_key: str\\n+    grain: str              # \\\"daily\\\" | \\\"weekly\\\" | \\\"monthly\\\"\\n+    window_start: str       # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\\n+    window_end: str         # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\\n+    observed_on: str        # ISO timestamp YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ\\n+    value_num: float | None\\n+    run_id: str\\n+    preliminary: bool\\n+    video_id: str | None = None\\n+\\n+\\n+def _table_for(video_id: str | None) -> str:\\n+    return \\\"video_metric_snapshots\\\" if video_id is not None else \\\"channel_metric_snapshots\\\"\\n+\\n+\\n+def write_snapshot_batch(conn: sqlite3.Connection, rows: Iterable[SnapshotRow]) -> int:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Insert snapshot rows in a single transaction.\\n+\\n+    Uses `INSERT OR IGNORE` so idempotent re-runs with the same\\n+    (entity, metric, window, observed_on) PK are no-ops rather than errors.\\n+    A fresh `observed_on` (usually the ingest run's wall-clock) produces a\\n+    genuinely new row even if the other 4 columns match a prior snapshot \\u2014\\n+    this is the append-only semantics.\\n+\\n+    Returns the count of rows actually inserted (re-runs return 0).\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    rows = list(rows)\\n+    if not rows:\\n+        return 0\\n+\\n+    inserted = 0\\n+    conn.execute(\\\"BEGIN IMMEDIATE\\\")\\n+    try:\\n+        for r in rows:\\n+            table = _table_for(r.video_id)\\n+            if r.video_id is not None:\\n+                cur = conn.execute(\\n+                    f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\\n+                        (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\\n+                    \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+                    (\\n+                        r.video_id, r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start,\\n+                        r.window_end, r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\\n+                    ),\\n+                )\\n+            else:\\n+                cur = conn.execute(\\n+                    f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\\n+                        (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\\n+                    \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+                    (\\n+                        r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start, r.window_end,\\n+                        r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\\n+                    ),\\n+                )\\n+            inserted += cur.rowcount\\n+        conn.execute(\\\"COMMIT\\\")\\n+    except Exception:\\n+        try:\\n+            conn.execute(\\\"ROLLBACK\\\")\\n+        except sqlite3.OperationalError:\\n+            pass\\n+        raise\\n+    return inserted\\n+\\n+\\n+def latest_snapshot(\\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\\n+    *,\\n+    metric_key: str,\\n+    grain: str,\\n+    window_start: str,\\n+    window_end: str,\\n+    video_id: str | None = None,\\n+) -> sqlite3.Row | None:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the most recently observed snapshot for this (entity, metric, window).\\n+\\n+    Uses the `idx_channel_metric_latest` / `idx_video_metric_latest`\\n+    indexes declared in migration 001 for O(log n) lookup.\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    table = _table_for(video_id)\\n+    if video_id is not None:\\n+        row = conn.execute(\\n+            f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\\n+            WHERE video_id = ? AND metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\\n+            LIMIT 1\\n+            \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+            (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    else:\\n+        row = conn.execute(\\n+            f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\\n+            WHERE metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\\n+            LIMIT 1\\n+            \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+            (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    return row\\n+\\n+\\n+def count_snapshots(\\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\\n+    *,\\n+    table: str,\\n+    metric_key: str | None = None,\\n+) -> int:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Utility for ops/tests \\u2014 count rows, optionally filtered by metric.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    if metric_key is None:\\n+        return conn.execute(f\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table}\\\").fetchone()[0]\\n+    return conn.execute(\\n+        f\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table} WHERE metric_key = ?\\\",\\n+        (metric_key,),\\n+    ).fetchone()[0]\\n@@ -0,0 +1,73 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"First-run backfill \\u2014 one-shot 45-day historical pull.\\n+\\n+Runs exactly once on a fresh deployment. Detects emptiness of\\n+channel_metric_snapshots; if fewer than FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD rows, pulls the\\n+last 45 days of weekly data via repeated calls to run_daily_refresh.\\n+\\n+Entry point for task-08 install script: `python -m ingest.first_run`.\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import logging\\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\\n+\\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\\n+from app.repositories.metrics import count_snapshots\\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\\n+\\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\\n+\\n+BACKFILL_DAYS = 45\\n+FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD = 7  # <this many rows means we haven't backfilled\\n+\\n+\\n+def needs_first_run() -> bool:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"True iff channel_metric_snapshots is near-empty.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\\n+        count = count_snapshots(conn, table=\\\"channel_metric_snapshots\\\")\\n+    return count < FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD\\n+\\n+\\n+def run_first_time_backfill(*, client=None, today: date | None = None) -> int:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Pull BACKFILL_DAYS of daily data. Returns count of ingest runs completed.\\n+\\n+    Iterates target_date from (today - BACKFILL_DAYS) up to (today - 2),\\n+    calling run_daily_refresh() once per target date. Aborts on quota\\n+    exhaustion (leaves remaining days for the next invocation).\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\\n+    first_target = today - timedelta(days=BACKFILL_DAYS)\\n+    last_target = today - timedelta(days=2)\\n+\\n+    runs_completed = 0\\n+    current = first_target\\n+    while current <= last_target:\\n+        result = run_daily_refresh(current, client=client, today=today)\\n+        runs_completed += 1\\n+        _LOG.info(\\n+            \\\"first_run backfill day=%s run_id=%s status=%s rows=%d\\\",\\n+            current.isoformat(),\\n+            result.run_id,\\n+            result.status,\\n+            result.rows_written,\\n+        )\\n+        if result.status == \\\"quota_exhausted\\\":\\n+            _LOG.warning(\\\"first_run aborted at %s (quota exhausted)\\\", current.isoformat())\\n+            break\\n+        current += timedelta(days=1)\\n+    return runs_completed\\n+\\n+\\n+def main() -> int:\\n+    logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO, format=\\\"[first_run] %(message)s\\\")\\n+    if not needs_first_run():\\n+        print(\\\"[first_run] channel_metric_snapshots already populated; no-op.\\\")\\n+        return 0\\n+    completed = run_first_time_backfill()\\n+    print(f\\\"[first_run] backfill completed: {completed} daily runs\\\")\\n+    return 0\\n+\\n+\\n+if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n+    raise SystemExit(main())\\n@@ -0,0 +1,226 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Daily ingest job entry point \\u2014 pulls YouTube metrics into the append-only\\n+snapshot tables.\\n+\\n+Invoked by:\\n+  - scripts/run_refresh.py (task-08 cron) \\u2014 daily 03:30 GMT+3 production run\\n+  - ingest/first_run.py (task-03) \\u2014 initial 45-day backfill\\n+\\n+Semantics:\\n+  - Target date = `today - 2` by default (YouTube Analytics 2-day freshness lag).\\n+  - Preliminary flag = true for rows observed <3 days after window_end.\\n+  - Append-only: every invocation writes NEW rows with fresh `observed_on`.\\n+  - Idempotent on (video_id, metric, window, observed_on) PK \\u2014 re-runs inside\\n+    the same second are no-ops via `INSERT OR IGNORE`.\\n+\\n+Exit-code semantics (returned as int to callers):\\n+  0  \\u2014 success, all intended rows written\\n+  1  \\u2014 YouTube API transient failure after retries exhausted\\n+  2  \\u2014 sqlite / repository failure\\n+  3  \\u2014 partial success (channel rows landed, per-video had issues)\\n+  40 \\u2014 quota exhausted (HTTP 429), next-day reschedule recommended\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import logging\\n+import sqlite3\\n+import uuid\\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\\n+\\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\\n+\\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\\n+\\n+# YouTube Analytics has a 2-day freshness lag; pulls for today generally\\n+# return incomplete data. Default pull targets `today - PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS`\\n+# and marks observations as preliminary for < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS old.\\n+PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS = 2\\n+PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS = 3\\n+\\n+# Channel-level weekly metrics we always pull in the daily refresh.\\n+CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS = (\\n+    \\\"views\\\",\\n+    \\\"estimatedMinutesWatched\\\",\\n+    \\\"averageViewDuration\\\",\\n+    \\\"averageViewPercentage\\\",\\n+    \\\"impressions\\\",\\n+    \\\"impressionsClickThroughRate\\\",\\n+    \\\"subscribersGained\\\",\\n+    \\\"subscribersLost\\\",\\n+)\\n+\\n+\\n+@dataclass\\n+class RunResult:\\n+    run_id: str\\n+    status: str          # \\\"ok\\\" | \\\"partial\\\" | \\\"api_failure\\\" | \\\"db_failure\\\" | \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+    rows_written: int\\n+    error_text: str | None = None\\n+\\n+\\n+def _now_iso() -> str:\\n+    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\\\")\\n+\\n+\\n+def _week_window(target_date: date) -> tuple[str, str]:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"ISO-week window ending on target_date's week. Returns (start, end) YYYY-MM-DD.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    # ISO week starts Monday; compute the Monday of target_date's ISO week\\n+    # and the Sunday that closes it.\\n+    weekday = target_date.isoweekday()  # 1=Mon..7=Sun\\n+    monday = target_date - timedelta(days=weekday - 1)\\n+    sunday = monday + timedelta(days=6)\\n+    return monday.isoformat(), sunday.isoformat()\\n+\\n+\\n+def _is_preliminary(target_date: date, today: date) -> bool:\\n+    return (today - target_date).days < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS\\n+\\n+\\n+def _open_ingestion_run(conn: sqlite3.Connection, source: str) -> str:\\n+    run_id = f\\\"run-{uuid.uuid4().hex[:12]}\\\"\\n+    conn.execute(\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+        INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status)\\n+        VALUES (?, ?, ?, 'in_progress')\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+        (run_id, source, _now_iso()),\\n+    )\\n+    return run_id\\n+\\n+\\n+def _close_ingestion_run(\\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\\n+    run_id: str,\\n+    status: str,\\n+    *,\\n+    quota_units: int | None = None,\\n+    error_text: str | None = None,\\n+) -> None:\\n+    conn.execute(\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+        UPDATE ingestion_runs\\n+        SET finished_at = ?, status = ?, quota_units = ?, error_text = ?\\n+        WHERE run_id = ?\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+        (_now_iso(), status, quota_units, error_text, run_id),\\n+    )\\n+\\n+\\n+def run_daily_refresh(\\n+    target_date: date | None = None,\\n+    *,\\n+    client=None,\\n+    today: date | None = None,\\n+) -> RunResult:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Pull one day's worth of YouTube metrics into snapshot tables.\\n+\\n+    Args:\\n+        target_date: the day whose data we're pulling. Default: today-2.\\n+        client: optional YouTubeClient; if None, a fresh one is instantiated.\\n+            Accepting a client parameter makes tests trivial \\u2014 fixtures pass\\n+            a mock that answers .get_channel_analytics / .get_retention.\\n+        today: injected \\\"today\\\" (defaults to UTC date). Tests pin it.\\n+\\n+    Returns a RunResult with status + rows_written + optional error_text.\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\\n+    target_date = target_date or (today - timedelta(days=PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS))\\n+    preliminary = _is_preliminary(target_date, today)\\n+\\n+    # Lazy client construction so unit tests that pass their own `client`\\n+    # never need google-auth installed on the path.\\n+    if client is None:\\n+        from ingest.youtube_client import YouTubeClient  # noqa: WPS433\\n+\\n+        client = YouTubeClient()\\n+\\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\\n+        run_id = _open_ingestion_run(conn, source=\\\"daily_refresh\\\")\\n+        try:\\n+            week_start, week_end = _week_window(target_date)\\n+            analytics = client.get_channel_analytics(\\n+                start_date=week_start,\\n+                end_date=week_end,\\n+                metrics=\\\",\\\".join(CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS),\\n+                run_id=run_id,\\n+            )\\n+            rows = list(_analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\\n+                analytics,\\n+                grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+                window_start=week_start,\\n+                window_end=week_end,\\n+                run_id=run_id,\\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\\n+            ))\\n+            try:\\n+                written = write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\\n+            except sqlite3.Error as db_exc:\\n+                _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \\\"db_failure\\\", error_text=str(db_exc))\\n+                return RunResult(run_id, \\\"db_failure\\\", 0, str(db_exc))\\n+\\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \\\"ok\\\")\\n+            return RunResult(run_id, \\\"ok\\\", written)\\n+        except Exception as api_exc:  # noqa: BLE001 \\u2014 catch-all to record in run log\\n+            status = _classify_api_exception(api_exc)\\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, status, error_text=str(api_exc))\\n+            return RunResult(run_id, status, 0, str(api_exc))\\n+\\n+\\n+def _analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\\n+    analytics: dict,\\n+    *,\\n+    grain: str,\\n+    window_start: str,\\n+    window_end: str,\\n+    run_id: str,\\n+    preliminary: bool,\\n+):\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Translate a YouTube Analytics reports.query() response into SnapshotRows.\\n+\\n+    YouTube Analytics response shape:\\n+      {\\n+        \\\"columnHeaders\\\": [{\\\"name\\\": \\\"views\\\", ...}, ...],\\n+        \\\"rows\\\": [[412, 1189, 173, 24.8, ...]]  # single row for channel-total\\n+      }\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    headers = analytics.get(\\\"columnHeaders\\\", [])\\n+    rows = analytics.get(\\\"rows\\\") or []\\n+    if not rows:\\n+        return\\n+    metric_names = [h[\\\"name\\\"] for h in headers if h.get(\\\"columnType\\\") != \\\"DIMENSION\\\"]\\n+    # Channel-total query returns exactly one row; per-video would have many.\\n+    observed_on = _now_iso()\\n+    for data_row in rows:\\n+        # Skip any dimension columns \\u2014 we only wrote metric-only queries here.\\n+        for idx, metric_name in enumerate(metric_names):\\n+            value = data_row[idx]\\n+            try:\\n+                value_num = float(value) if value is not None else None\\n+            except (TypeError, ValueError):\\n+                value_num = None\\n+            yield SnapshotRow(\\n+                metric_key=metric_name,\\n+                grain=grain,\\n+                window_start=window_start,\\n+                window_end=window_end,\\n+                observed_on=observed_on,\\n+                value_num=value_num,\\n+                run_id=run_id,\\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\\n+                video_id=None,  # channel-level\\n+            )\\n+\\n+\\n+def _classify_api_exception(exc: BaseException) -> str:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Map raised exceptions from YouTubeClient to run status strings.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    try:\\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\\n+    except ImportError:\\n+        return \\\"api_failure\\\"\\n+    if isinstance(exc, HttpError):\\n+        status = int(getattr(exc, \\\"status_code\\\", 0) or getattr(exc.resp, \\\"status\\\", 0) or 0)\\n+        if status == 429:\\n+            return \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+    return \\\"api_failure\\\"\\n@@ -0,0 +1,200 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Tests for ingest.jobs.run_daily_refresh + ingest.first_run.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+from datetime import date\\n+from unittest.mock import MagicMock\\n+\\n+import pytest\\n+\\n+from app import db as dbmod\\n+from ingest import jobs\\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\\n+\\n+\\n+@pytest.fixture\\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \\\"test.sqlite\\\"\\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\\\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\\\", str(db_file))\\n+    dbmod.migrate()\\n+    yield db_file\\n+\\n+\\n+def _fake_analytics_response(views=412, ctr=0.0463):\\n+    return {\\n+        \\\"columnHeaders\\\": [\\n+            {\\\"name\\\": \\\"views\\\", \\\"columnType\\\": \\\"METRIC\\\", \\\"dataType\\\": \\\"INTEGER\\\"},\\n+            {\\\"name\\\": \\\"impressionsClickThroughRate\\\", \\\"columnType\\\": \\\"METRIC\\\", \\\"dataType\\\": \\\"FLOAT\\\"},\\n+        ],\\n+        \\\"rows\\\": [[views, ctr]],\\n+    }\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_happy_path(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    assert result.rows_written == 2  # 2 metrics x 1 row\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        rows = list(conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT metric_key, value_num, preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots\\\"\\n+            \\\" ORDER BY metric_key\\\"\\n+        ))\\n+    keys = [r[\\\"metric_key\\\"] for r in rows]\\n+    assert \\\"views\\\" in keys\\n+    assert \\\"impressionsClickThroughRate\\\" in keys\\n+    # 2026-04-22 minus 2-day lag = target 2026-04-20 \\u2192 2 days ago \\u2192 NOT preliminary\\n+    # (< 3 days OLD would be preliminary; 2 days back IS preliminary per < 3 rule)\\n+    assert rows[0][\\\"preliminary\\\"] == 1  # preliminary flag set\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_not_preliminary_after_window(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+    # Pull a date well in the past (>3 days) \\u2014 preliminary=False\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 10),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        row = conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots LIMIT 1\\\"\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    assert row[\\\"preliminary\\\"] == 0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_records_ingestion_run(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        run_row = conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT status, started_at, finished_at FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\\\",\\n+            (result.run_id,),\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    assert run_row[\\\"status\\\"] == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    assert run_row[\\\"started_at\\\"] is not None\\n+    assert run_row[\\\"finished_at\\\"] is not None\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_quota_exhausted(fresh_db):\\n+    try:\\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\\n+    except ImportError:\\n+        pytest.skip(\\\"google-api-python-client not installed\\\")\\n+\\n+    class FakeResp:\\n+        status = 429\\n+        reason = \\\"quota\\\"\\n+\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\\\"quota\\\")\\n+\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\\n+    # ingestion_runs must record the failure.\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        status = conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT status FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\\\",\\n+            (result.run_id,),\\n+        ).fetchone()[0]\\n+    assert status == \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_empty_response_writes_nothing(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = {\\\"columnHeaders\\\": [], \\\"rows\\\": []}\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_first_run_backfill_skipped_when_populated(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\\n+    from ingest import first_run\\n+\\n+    # Pre-populate the table past FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD.\\n+    from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \\\"\\n+            \\\"VALUES ('seed', 'test', '2026-04-20T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\\\",\\n+        )\\n+        rows = [\\n+            SnapshotRow(\\\"views\\\", \\\"weekly\\\", \\\"2026-04-01\\\", \\\"2026-04-07\\\",\\n+                         f\\\"2026-04-22T0{i}:00:00Z\\\", 10.0, \\\"seed\\\", False)\\n+            for i in range(first_run.FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD + 1)\\n+        ]\\n+        write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\\n+\\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is False\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_first_run_backfill_fires_on_empty_db(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\\n+    from ingest import first_run\\n+\\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is True\\n+\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+\\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    # BACKFILL_DAYS=45, last_target = today-2 = 2026-04-20.\\n+    # First target = 2026-04-22 - 45 = 2026-03-08. Range is inclusive: 44 days.\\n+    assert count == 44\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        runs = conn.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ingestion_runs\\\").fetchone()[0]\\n+    assert runs == 44\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_first_run_aborts_on_quota(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\\n+    try:\\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\\n+    except ImportError:\\n+        pytest.skip(\\\"google-api-python-client not installed\\\")\\n+\\n+    from ingest import first_run\\n+\\n+    class FakeResp:\\n+        status = 429\\n+        reason = \\\"quota\\\"\\n+\\n+    call_count = {\\\"n\\\": 0}\\n+\\n+    def flaky_get(**_kwargs):\\n+        call_count[\\\"n\\\"] += 1\\n+        if call_count[\\\"n\\\"] >= 3:\\n+            raise HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\\\"quota\\\")\\n+        return _fake_analytics_response()\\n+\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = flaky_get\\n+\\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    # 2 successful + 1 that raises = 3 runs attempted, loop breaks after the quota error.\\n+    assert count == 3\\n@@ -0,0 +1,141 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Tests for app.repositories.metrics \\u2014 append-only snapshot semantics.\\n+\\n+Covers:\\n+  - Single-row insert round-trip.\\n+  - Re-run with same PK = no-op (INSERT OR IGNORE).\\n+  - Re-run with fresh observed_on = new row appended.\\n+  - latest_snapshot returns the most recent row.\\n+  - Channel vs per-video row routing.\\n+  - FK enforcement: writing a video_metric row without a matching videos entry fails.\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import pytest\\n+\\n+from app import db as dbmod\\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, latest_snapshot, write_snapshot_batch\\n+\\n+\\n+@pytest.fixture\\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \\\"test.sqlite\\\"\\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\\\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\\\", str(db_file))\\n+    dbmod.migrate()\\n+    # Open a single connection reused across assertions in the test for\\n+    # simplicity (each test gets its own tmp DB via fresh_db fixture).\\n+    conn = None\\n+    try:\\n+        ctx = dbmod.connect()\\n+        conn = ctx.__enter__()\\n+        # Seed an ingestion_runs row so our writes satisfy the FK.\\n+        conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \\\"\\n+            \\\"VALUES (?, 'test', '2026-04-21T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\\\",\\n+            (\\\"run-test\\\",),\\n+        )\\n+        yield conn\\n+    finally:\\n+        if conn is not None:\\n+            try:\\n+                ctx.__exit__(None, None, None)  # type: ignore[name-defined]\\n+            except Exception:\\n+                pass\\n+\\n+\\n+def _row(observed_on: str, metric: str = \\\"views\\\", value: float = 100.0) -> SnapshotRow:\\n+    return SnapshotRow(\\n+        metric_key=metric,\\n+        grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\",\\n+        window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        observed_on=observed_on,\\n+        value_num=value,\\n+        run_id=\\\"run-test\\\",\\n+        preliminary=True,\\n+        video_id=None,\\n+    )\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_channel_snapshot_round_trip(fresh_db):\\n+    inserted = write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=412)])\\n+    assert inserted == 1\\n+    found = latest_snapshot(\\n+        fresh_db,\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\", grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\", window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    assert found is not None\\n+    assert found[\\\"value_num\\\"] == 412.0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_same_observed_on_is_noop(fresh_db):\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=412)]) == 1\\n+    # Same PK columns \\u2014 INSERT OR IGNORE should drop it.\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=999)]) == 0\\n+    row = latest_snapshot(\\n+        fresh_db,\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\", grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\", window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    # First value wins.\\n+    assert row[\\\"value_num\\\"] == 412.0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_fresh_observed_on_appends_new_row(fresh_db):\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=412)]) == 1\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\\\", value=500)]) == 1\\n+    latest = latest_snapshot(\\n+        fresh_db,\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\", grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\", window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    assert latest[\\\"observed_on\\\"] == \\\"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\\\"\\n+    assert latest[\\\"value_num\\\"] == 500.0\\n+    # Both rows persist in history.\\n+    cnt = fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0]\\n+    assert cnt == 2\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_video_row_routes_to_video_table(fresh_db):\\n+    # Seed a videos row so FK succeeds.\\n+    fresh_db.execute(\\n+        \\\"INSERT INTO videos (video_id, title) VALUES ('vXYZ', 'Test')\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    video_row = SnapshotRow(\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\",\\n+        grain=\\\"daily\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        observed_on=\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\",\\n+        value_num=55,\\n+        run_id=\\\"run-test\\\",\\n+        preliminary=False,\\n+        video_id=\\\"vXYZ\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [video_row]) == 1\\n+    # Channel table should be empty; video table has the row.\\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0] == 0\\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0] == 1\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_video_row_without_videos_entry_fk_fails(fresh_db):\\n+    bad = SnapshotRow(\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\",\\n+        grain=\\\"daily\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        observed_on=\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\",\\n+        value_num=55,\\n+        run_id=\\\"run-test\\\",\\n+        preliminary=False,\\n+        video_id=\\\"nonexistent\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    with pytest.raises(Exception):  # sqlite3.IntegrityError wrapped at executemany\\n+        write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [bad])\\n+    # Transaction rolled back.\\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0] == 0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_empty_batch_returns_zero(fresh_db):\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, []) == 0\", \"files\": [{\"filename\": \"app/repositories/__init__.py\", \"patch\": null}, {\"filename\": \"app/repositories/metrics.py\", \"patch\": \"@@ -0,0 +1,158 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Metrics repository \\u2014 append-only snapshot reads and writes.\\n+\\n+Append-only invariant:\\n+  - Every snapshot row is identified by (entity, metric_key, grain, window,\\n+    observed_on). Re-pulls emit a NEW row with fresh `observed_on`.\\n+  - Dashboard reads select the latest row per (entity, metric_key, window)\\n+    via MAX(observed_on).\\n+  - Preliminary-flag handling: when YouTube's 2-day-lag window resettles\\n+    with stable values, caller may mark prior preliminary rows as stable by\\n+    writing a new row with preliminary=0; the legacy preliminary row stays\\n+    for audit.\\n+\\n+Consumed by: ingest/jobs.py (task-03 writer), dashboard views (task-06+).\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import sqlite3\\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\\n+from typing import Iterable\\n+\\n+\\n+@dataclass(frozen=True)\\n+class SnapshotRow:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Single append-only metric observation.\\n+\\n+    video_id == None marks a channel-level snapshot (stored in\\n+    channel_metric_snapshots). Otherwise the row lives in\\n+    video_metric_snapshots.\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+    metric_key: str\\n+    grain: str              # \\\"daily\\\" | \\\"weekly\\\" | \\\"monthly\\\"\\n+    window_start: str       # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\\n+    window_end: str         # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\\n+    observed_on: str        # ISO timestamp YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ\\n+    value_num: float | None\\n+    run_id: str\\n+    preliminary: bool\\n+    video_id: str | None = None\\n+\\n+\\n+def _table_for(video_id: str | None) -> str:\\n+    return \\\"video_metric_snapshots\\\" if video_id is not None else \\\"channel_metric_snapshots\\\"\\n+\\n+\\n+def write_snapshot_batch(conn: sqlite3.Connection, rows: Iterable[SnapshotRow]) -> int:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Insert snapshot rows in a single transaction.\\n+\\n+    Uses `INSERT OR IGNORE` so idempotent re-runs with the same\\n+    (entity, metric, window, observed_on) PK are no-ops rather than errors.\\n+    A fresh `observed_on` (usually the ingest run's wall-clock) produces a\\n+    genuinely new row even if the other 4 columns match a prior snapshot \\u2014\\n+    this is the append-only semantics.\\n+\\n+    Returns the count of rows actually inserted (re-runs return 0).\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    rows = list(rows)\\n+    if not rows:\\n+        return 0\\n+\\n+    inserted = 0\\n+    conn.execute(\\\"BEGIN IMMEDIATE\\\")\\n+    try:\\n+        for r in rows:\\n+            table = _table_for(r.video_id)\\n+            if r.video_id is not None:\\n+                cur = conn.execute(\\n+                    f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\\n+                        (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\\n+                    \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+                    (\\n+                        r.video_id, r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start,\\n+                        r.window_end, r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\\n+                    ),\\n+                )\\n+            else:\\n+                cur = conn.execute(\\n+                    f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\\n+                        (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\\n+                    \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+                    (\\n+                        r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start, r.window_end,\\n+                        r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\\n+                    ),\\n+                )\\n+            inserted += cur.rowcount\\n+        conn.execute(\\\"COMMIT\\\")\\n+    except Exception:\\n+        try:\\n+            conn.execute(\\\"ROLLBACK\\\")\\n+        except sqlite3.OperationalError:\\n+            pass\\n+        raise\\n+    return inserted\\n+\\n+\\n+def latest_snapshot(\\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\\n+    *,\\n+    metric_key: str,\\n+    grain: str,\\n+    window_start: str,\\n+    window_end: str,\\n+    video_id: str | None = None,\\n+) -> sqlite3.Row | None:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the most recently observed snapshot for this (entity, metric, window).\\n+\\n+    Uses the `idx_channel_metric_latest` / `idx_video_metric_latest`\\n+    indexes declared in migration 001 for O(log n) lookup.\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    table = _table_for(video_id)\\n+    if video_id is not None:\\n+        row = conn.execute(\\n+            f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\\n+            WHERE video_id = ? AND metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\\n+            LIMIT 1\\n+            \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+            (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    else:\\n+        row = conn.execute(\\n+            f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\\n+            WHERE metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\\n+            LIMIT 1\\n+            \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+            (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    return row\\n+\\n+\\n+def count_snapshots(\\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\\n+    *,\\n+    table: str,\\n+    metric_key: str | None = None,\\n+) -> int:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Utility for ops/tests \\u2014 count rows, optionally filtered by metric.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    if metric_key is None:\\n+        return conn.execute(f\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table}\\\").fetchone()[0]\\n+    return conn.execute(\\n+        f\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table} WHERE metric_key = ?\\\",\\n+        (metric_key,),\\n+    ).fetchone()[0]\"}, {\"filename\": \"ingest/first_run.py\", \"patch\": \"@@ -0,0 +1,73 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"First-run backfill \\u2014 one-shot 45-day historical pull.\\n+\\n+Runs exactly once on a fresh deployment. Detects emptiness of\\n+channel_metric_snapshots; if fewer than FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD rows, pulls the\\n+last 45 days of weekly data via repeated calls to run_daily_refresh.\\n+\\n+Entry point for task-08 install script: `python -m ingest.first_run`.\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import logging\\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\\n+\\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\\n+from app.repositories.metrics import count_snapshots\\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\\n+\\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\\n+\\n+BACKFILL_DAYS = 45\\n+FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD = 7  # <this many rows means we haven't backfilled\\n+\\n+\\n+def needs_first_run() -> bool:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"True iff channel_metric_snapshots is near-empty.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\\n+        count = count_snapshots(conn, table=\\\"channel_metric_snapshots\\\")\\n+    return count < FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD\\n+\\n+\\n+def run_first_time_backfill(*, client=None, today: date | None = None) -> int:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Pull BACKFILL_DAYS of daily data. Returns count of ingest runs completed.\\n+\\n+    Iterates target_date from (today - BACKFILL_DAYS) up to (today - 2),\\n+    calling run_daily_refresh() once per target date. Aborts on quota\\n+    exhaustion (leaves remaining days for the next invocation).\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\\n+    first_target = today - timedelta(days=BACKFILL_DAYS)\\n+    last_target = today - timedelta(days=2)\\n+\\n+    runs_completed = 0\\n+    current = first_target\\n+    while current <= last_target:\\n+        result = run_daily_refresh(current, client=client, today=today)\\n+        runs_completed += 1\\n+        _LOG.info(\\n+            \\\"first_run backfill day=%s run_id=%s status=%s rows=%d\\\",\\n+            current.isoformat(),\\n+            result.run_id,\\n+            result.status,\\n+            result.rows_written,\\n+        )\\n+        if result.status == \\\"quota_exhausted\\\":\\n+            _LOG.warning(\\\"first_run aborted at %s (quota exhausted)\\\", current.isoformat())\\n+            break\\n+        current += timedelta(days=1)\\n+    return runs_completed\\n+\\n+\\n+def main() -> int:\\n+    logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO, format=\\\"[first_run] %(message)s\\\")\\n+    if not needs_first_run():\\n+        print(\\\"[first_run] channel_metric_snapshots already populated; no-op.\\\")\\n+        return 0\\n+    completed = run_first_time_backfill()\\n+    print(f\\\"[first_run] backfill completed: {completed} daily runs\\\")\\n+    return 0\\n+\\n+\\n+if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n+    raise SystemExit(main())\"}, {\"filename\": \"ingest/jobs.py\", \"patch\": \"@@ -0,0 +1,226 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Daily ingest job entry point \\u2014 pulls YouTube metrics into the append-only\\n+snapshot tables.\\n+\\n+Invoked by:\\n+  - scripts/run_refresh.py (task-08 cron) \\u2014 daily 03:30 GMT+3 production run\\n+  - ingest/first_run.py (task-03) \\u2014 initial 45-day backfill\\n+\\n+Semantics:\\n+  - Target date = `today - 2` by default (YouTube Analytics 2-day freshness lag).\\n+  - Preliminary flag = true for rows observed <3 days after window_end.\\n+  - Append-only: every invocation writes NEW rows with fresh `observed_on`.\\n+  - Idempotent on (video_id, metric, window, observed_on) PK \\u2014 re-runs inside\\n+    the same second are no-ops via `INSERT OR IGNORE`.\\n+\\n+Exit-code semantics (returned as int to callers):\\n+  0  \\u2014 success, all intended rows written\\n+  1  \\u2014 YouTube API transient failure after retries exhausted\\n+  2  \\u2014 sqlite / repository failure\\n+  3  \\u2014 partial success (channel rows landed, per-video had issues)\\n+  40 \\u2014 quota exhausted (HTTP 429), next-day reschedule recommended\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import logging\\n+import sqlite3\\n+import uuid\\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\\n+\\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\\n+\\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\\n+\\n+# YouTube Analytics has a 2-day freshness lag; pulls for today generally\\n+# return incomplete data. Default pull targets `today - PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS`\\n+# and marks observations as preliminary for < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS old.\\n+PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS = 2\\n+PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS = 3\\n+\\n+# Channel-level weekly metrics we always pull in the daily refresh.\\n+CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS = (\\n+    \\\"views\\\",\\n+    \\\"estimatedMinutesWatched\\\",\\n+    \\\"averageViewDuration\\\",\\n+    \\\"averageViewPercentage\\\",\\n+    \\\"impressions\\\",\\n+    \\\"impressionsClickThroughRate\\\",\\n+    \\\"subscribersGained\\\",\\n+    \\\"subscribersLost\\\",\\n+)\\n+\\n+\\n+@dataclass\\n+class RunResult:\\n+    run_id: str\\n+    status: str          # \\\"ok\\\" | \\\"partial\\\" | \\\"api_failure\\\" | \\\"db_failure\\\" | \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+    rows_written: int\\n+    error_text: str | None = None\\n+\\n+\\n+def _now_iso() -> str:\\n+    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\\\")\\n+\\n+\\n+def _week_window(target_date: date) -> tuple[str, str]:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"ISO-week window ending on target_date's week. Returns (start, end) YYYY-MM-DD.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    # ISO week starts Monday; compute the Monday of target_date's ISO week\\n+    # and the Sunday that closes it.\\n+    weekday = target_date.isoweekday()  # 1=Mon..7=Sun\\n+    monday = target_date - timedelta(days=weekday - 1)\\n+    sunday = monday + timedelta(days=6)\\n+    return monday.isoformat(), sunday.isoformat()\\n+\\n+\\n+def _is_preliminary(target_date: date, today: date) -> bool:\\n+    return (today - target_date).days < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS\\n+\\n+\\n+def _open_ingestion_run(conn: sqlite3.Connection, source: str) -> str:\\n+    run_id = f\\\"run-{uuid.uuid4().hex[:12]}\\\"\\n+    conn.execute(\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+        INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status)\\n+        VALUES (?, ?, ?, 'in_progress')\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+        (run_id, source, _now_iso()),\\n+    )\\n+    return run_id\\n+\\n+\\n+def _close_ingestion_run(\\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\\n+    run_id: str,\\n+    status: str,\\n+    *,\\n+    quota_units: int | None = None,\\n+    error_text: str | None = None,\\n+) -> None:\\n+    conn.execute(\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+        UPDATE ingestion_runs\\n+        SET finished_at = ?, status = ?, quota_units = ?, error_text = ?\\n+        WHERE run_id = ?\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+        (_now_iso(), status, quota_units, error_text, run_id),\\n+    )\\n+\\n+\\n+def run_daily_refresh(\\n+    target_date: date | None = None,\\n+    *,\\n+    client=None,\\n+    today: date | None = None,\\n+) -> RunResult:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Pull one day's worth of YouTube metrics into snapshot tables.\\n+\\n+    Args:\\n+        target_date: the day whose data we're pulling. Default: today-2.\\n+        client: optional YouTubeClient; if None, a fresh one is instantiated.\\n+            Accepting a client parameter makes tests trivial \\u2014 fixtures pass\\n+            a mock that answers .get_channel_analytics / .get_retention.\\n+        today: injected \\\"today\\\" (defaults to UTC date). Tests pin it.\\n+\\n+    Returns a RunResult with status + rows_written + optional error_text.\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\\n+    target_date = target_date or (today - timedelta(days=PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS))\\n+    preliminary = _is_preliminary(target_date, today)\\n+\\n+    # Lazy client construction so unit tests that pass their own `client`\\n+    # never need google-auth installed on the path.\\n+    if client is None:\\n+        from ingest.youtube_client import YouTubeClient  # noqa: WPS433\\n+\\n+        client = YouTubeClient()\\n+\\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\\n+        run_id = _open_ingestion_run(conn, source=\\\"daily_refresh\\\")\\n+        try:\\n+            week_start, week_end = _week_window(target_date)\\n+            analytics = client.get_channel_analytics(\\n+                start_date=week_start,\\n+                end_date=week_end,\\n+                metrics=\\\",\\\".join(CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS),\\n+                run_id=run_id,\\n+            )\\n+            rows = list(_analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\\n+                analytics,\\n+                grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+                window_start=week_start,\\n+                window_end=week_end,\\n+                run_id=run_id,\\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\\n+            ))\\n+            try:\\n+                written = write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\\n+            except sqlite3.Error as db_exc:\\n+                _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \\\"db_failure\\\", error_text=str(db_exc))\\n+                return RunResult(run_id, \\\"db_failure\\\", 0, str(db_exc))\\n+\\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \\\"ok\\\")\\n+            return RunResult(run_id, \\\"ok\\\", written)\\n+        except Exception as api_exc:  # noqa: BLE001 \\u2014 catch-all to record in run log\\n+            status = _classify_api_exception(api_exc)\\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, status, error_text=str(api_exc))\\n+            return RunResult(run_id, status, 0, str(api_exc))\\n+\\n+\\n+def _analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\\n+    analytics: dict,\\n+    *,\\n+    grain: str,\\n+    window_start: str,\\n+    window_end: str,\\n+    run_id: str,\\n+    preliminary: bool,\\n+):\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Translate a YouTube Analytics reports.query() response into SnapshotRows.\\n+\\n+    YouTube Analytics response shape:\\n+      {\\n+        \\\"columnHeaders\\\": [{\\\"name\\\": \\\"views\\\", ...}, ...],\\n+        \\\"rows\\\": [[412, 1189, 173, 24.8, ...]]  # single row for channel-total\\n+      }\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    headers = analytics.get(\\\"columnHeaders\\\", [])\\n+    rows = analytics.get(\\\"rows\\\") or []\\n+    if not rows:\\n+        return\\n+    metric_names = [h[\\\"name\\\"] for h in headers if h.get(\\\"columnType\\\") != \\\"DIMENSION\\\"]\\n+    # Channel-total query returns exactly one row; per-video would have many.\\n+    observed_on = _now_iso()\\n+    for data_row in rows:\\n+        # Skip any dimension columns \\u2014 we only wrote metric-only queries here.\\n+        for idx, metric_name in enumerate(metric_names):\\n+            value = data_row[idx]\\n+            try:\\n+                value_num = float(value) if value is not None else None\\n+            except (TypeError, ValueError):\\n+                value_num = None\\n+            yield SnapshotRow(\\n+                metric_key=metric_name,\\n+                grain=grain,\\n+                window_start=window_start,\\n+                window_end=window_end,\\n+                observed_on=observed_on,\\n+                value_num=value_num,\\n+                run_id=run_id,\\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\\n+                video_id=None,  # channel-level\\n+            )\\n+\\n+\\n+def _classify_api_exception(exc: BaseException) -> str:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Map raised exceptions from YouTubeClient to run status strings.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    try:\\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\\n+    except ImportError:\\n+        return \\\"api_failure\\\"\\n+    if isinstance(exc, HttpError):\\n+        status = int(getattr(exc, \\\"status_code\\\", 0) or getattr(exc.resp, \\\"status\\\", 0) or 0)\\n+        if status == 429:\\n+            return \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+    return \\\"api_failure\\\"\"}, {\"filename\": \"tests/test_ingest_jobs.py\", \"patch\": \"@@ -0,0 +1,200 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Tests for ingest.jobs.run_daily_refresh + ingest.first_run.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+from datetime import date\\n+from unittest.mock import MagicMock\\n+\\n+import pytest\\n+\\n+from app import db as dbmod\\n+from ingest import jobs\\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\\n+\\n+\\n+@pytest.fixture\\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \\\"test.sqlite\\\"\\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\\\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\\\", str(db_file))\\n+    dbmod.migrate()\\n+    yield db_file\\n+\\n+\\n+def _fake_analytics_response(views=412, ctr=0.0463):\\n+    return {\\n+        \\\"columnHeaders\\\": [\\n+            {\\\"name\\\": \\\"views\\\", \\\"columnType\\\": \\\"METRIC\\\", \\\"dataType\\\": \\\"INTEGER\\\"},\\n+            {\\\"name\\\": \\\"impressionsClickThroughRate\\\", \\\"columnType\\\": \\\"METRIC\\\", \\\"dataType\\\": \\\"FLOAT\\\"},\\n+        ],\\n+        \\\"rows\\\": [[views, ctr]],\\n+    }\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_happy_path(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    assert result.rows_written == 2  # 2 metrics x 1 row\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        rows = list(conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT metric_key, value_num, preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots\\\"\\n+            \\\" ORDER BY metric_key\\\"\\n+        ))\\n+    keys = [r[\\\"metric_key\\\"] for r in rows]\\n+    assert \\\"views\\\" in keys\\n+    assert \\\"impressionsClickThroughRate\\\" in keys\\n+    # 2026-04-22 minus 2-day lag = target 2026-04-20 \\u2192 2 days ago \\u2192 NOT preliminary\\n+    # (< 3 days OLD would be preliminary; 2 days back IS preliminary per < 3 rule)\\n+    assert rows[0][\\\"preliminary\\\"] == 1  # preliminary flag set\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_not_preliminary_after_window(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+    # Pull a date well in the past (>3 days) \\u2014 preliminary=False\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 10),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        row = conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots LIMIT 1\\\"\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    assert row[\\\"preliminary\\\"] == 0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_records_ingestion_run(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        run_row = conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT status, started_at, finished_at FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\\\",\\n+            (result.run_id,),\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    assert run_row[\\\"status\\\"] == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    assert run_row[\\\"started_at\\\"] is not None\\n+    assert run_row[\\\"finished_at\\\"] is not None\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_quota_exhausted(fresh_db):\\n+    try:\\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\\n+    except ImportError:\\n+        pytest.skip(\\\"google-api-python-client not installed\\\")\\n+\\n+    class FakeResp:\\n+        status = 429\\n+        reason = \\\"quota\\\"\\n+\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\\\"quota\\\")\\n+\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\\n+    # ingestion_runs must record the failure.\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        status = conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT status FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\\\",\\n+            (result.run_id,),\\n+        ).fetchone()[0]\\n+    assert status == \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_empty_response_writes_nothing(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = {\\\"columnHeaders\\\": [], \\\"rows\\\": []}\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_first_run_backfill_skipped_when_populated(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\\n+    from ingest import first_run\\n+\\n+    # Pre-populate the table past FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD.\\n+    from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \\\"\\n+            \\\"VALUES ('seed', 'test', '2026-04-20T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\\\",\\n+        )\\n+        rows = [\\n+            SnapshotRow(\\\"views\\\", \\\"weekly\\\", \\\"2026-04-01\\\", \\\"2026-04-07\\\",\\n+                         f\\\"2026-04-22T0{i}:00:00Z\\\", 10.0, \\\"seed\\\", False)\\n+            for i in range(first_run.FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD + 1)\\n+        ]\\n+        write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\\n+\\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is False\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_first_run_backfill_fires_on_empty_db(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\\n+    from ingest import first_run\\n+\\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is True\\n+\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+\\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    # BACKFILL_DAYS=45, last_target = today-2 = 2026-04-20.\\n+    # First target = 2026-04-22 - 45 = 2026-03-08. Range is inclusive: 44 days.\\n+    assert count == 44\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        runs = conn.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ingestion_runs\\\").fetchone()[0]\\n+    assert runs == 44\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_first_run_aborts_on_quota(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\\n+    try:\\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\\n+    except ImportError:\\n+        pytest.skip(\\\"google-api-python-client not installed\\\")\\n+\\n+    from ingest import first_run\\n+\\n+    class FakeResp:\\n+        status = 429\\n+        reason = \\\"quota\\\"\\n+\\n+    call_count = {\\\"n\\\": 0}\\n+\\n+    def flaky_get(**_kwargs):\\n+        call_count[\\\"n\\\"] += 1\\n+        if call_count[\\\"n\\\"] >= 3:\\n+            raise HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\\\"quota\\\")\\n+        return _fake_analytics_response()\\n+\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = flaky_get\\n+\\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    # 2 successful + 1 that raises = 3 runs attempted, loop breaks after the quota error.\\n+    assert count == 3\"}, {\"filename\": \"tests/test_snapshot_append.py\", \"patch\": \"@@ -0,0 +1,141 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Tests for app.repositories.metrics \\u2014 append-only snapshot semantics.\\n+\\n+Covers:\\n+  - Single-row insert round-trip.\\n+  - Re-run with same PK = no-op (INSERT OR IGNORE).\\n+  - Re-run with fresh observed_on = new row appended.\\n+  - latest_snapshot returns the most recent row.\\n+  - Channel vs per-video row routing.\\n+  - FK enforcement: writing a video_metric row without a matching videos entry fails.\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import pytest\\n+\\n+from app import db as dbmod\\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, latest_snapshot, write_snapshot_batch\\n+\\n+\\n+@pytest.fixture\\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \\\"test.sqlite\\\"\\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\\\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\\\", str(db_file))\\n+    dbmod.migrate()\\n+    # Open a single connection reused across assertions in the test for\\n+    # simplicity (each test gets its own tmp DB via fresh_db fixture).\\n+    conn = None\\n+    try:\\n+        ctx = dbmod.connect()\\n+        conn = ctx.__enter__()\\n+        # Seed an ingestion_runs row so our writes satisfy the FK.\\n+        conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \\\"\\n+            \\\"VALUES (?, 'test', '2026-04-21T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\\\",\\n+            (\\\"run-test\\\",),\\n+        )\\n+        yield conn\\n+    finally:\\n+        if conn is not None:\\n+            try:\\n+                ctx.__exit__(None, None, None)  # type: ignore[name-defined]\\n+            except Exception:\\n+                pass\\n+\\n+\\n+def _row(observed_on: str, metric: str = \\\"views\\\", value: float = 100.0) -> SnapshotRow:\\n+    return SnapshotRow(\\n+        metric_key=metric,\\n+        grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\",\\n+        window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        observed_on=observed_on,\\n+        value_num=value,\\n+        run_id=\\\"run-test\\\",\\n+        preliminary=True,\\n+        video_id=None,\\n+    )\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_channel_snapshot_round_trip(fresh_db):\\n+    inserted = write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=412)])\\n+    assert inserted == 1\\n+    found = latest_snapshot(\\n+        fresh_db,\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\", grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\", window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    assert found is not None\\n+    assert found[\\\"value_num\\\"] == 412.0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_same_observed_on_is_noop(fresh_db):\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=412)]) == 1\\n+    # Same PK columns \\u2014 INSERT OR IGNORE should drop it.\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=999)]) == 0\\n+    row = latest_snapshot(\\n+        fresh_db,\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\", grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\", window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    # First value wins.\\n+    assert row[\\\"value_num\\\"] == 412.0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_fresh_observed_on_appends_new_row(fresh_db):\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=412)]) == 1\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\\\", value=500)]) == 1\\n+    latest = latest_snapshot(\\n+        fresh_db,\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\", grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\", window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    assert latest[\\\"observed_on\\\"] == \\\"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\\\"\\n+    assert latest[\\\"value_num\\\"] == 500.0\\n+    # Both rows persist in history.\\n+    cnt = fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0]\\n+    assert cnt == 2\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_video_row_routes_to_video_table(fresh_db):\\n+    # Seed a videos row so FK succeeds.\\n+    fresh_db.execute(\\n+        \\\"INSERT INTO videos (video_id, title) VALUES ('vXYZ', 'Test')\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    video_row = SnapshotRow(\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\",\\n+        grain=\\\"daily\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        observed_on=\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\",\\n+        value_num=55,\\n+        run_id=\\\"run-test\\\",\\n+        preliminary=False,\\n+        video_id=\\\"vXYZ\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [video_row]) == 1\\n+    # Channel table should be empty; video table has the row.\\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0] == 0\\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0] == 1\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_video_row_without_videos_entry_fk_fails(fresh_db):\\n+    bad = SnapshotRow(\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\",\\n+        grain=\\\"daily\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        observed_on=\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\",\\n+        value_num=55,\\n+        run_id=\\\"run-test\\\",\\n+        preliminary=False,\\n+        video_id=\\\"nonexistent\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    with pytest.raises(Exception):  # sqlite3.IntegrityError wrapped at executemany\\n+        write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [bad])\\n+    # Transaction rolled back.\\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0] == 0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_empty_batch_returns_zero(fresh_db):\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, []) == 0\"}], \"repository_full_name\": \"BlueRay2/history-production\", \"comments\": null, \"author\": {\"login\": \"Evander\", \"name\": null, \"email\": null, \"avatar_url\": \"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1937198?v=4\", \"id\": 1937198}, \"committer\": {\"login\": \"Evander\", \"name\": null, \"email\": null, \"avatar_url\": \"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1937198?v=4\", \"id\": 1937198}, \"created_at\": \"2026-04-21T22:00:21Z\", \"display_url\": \"https://github.com/BlueRay2/history-production/commit/ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810\", \"display_title\": \"task-03(kpi): append-snapshot ingest + first-run backfill + 14 tests\"}, \"url\": \"https://github.com/BlueRay2/history-production/commit/ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810\", \"title\": \"task-03(kpi): append-snapshot ingest + first-run backfill + 14 tests\\n\\nImplements task-03 per docs/tz/dashboard-kpi/task-03-append-snapshot-ingest.md.\\n\\n- app/repositories/metrics.py (140 LOC) \\u2014 SnapshotRow dataclass; write_snapshot_batch\\n  with INSERT OR IGNORE semantics inside BEGIN IMMEDIATE / COMMIT / ROLLBACK\\n  transaction; latest_snapshot with MAX(observed_on) via idx_*_metric_latest;\\n  count_snapshots ops helper. Append-only invariant documented: re-runs with\\n  fresh observed_on append new rows; same observed_on = no-op.\\n\\n- ingest/jobs.py (140 LOC) \\u2014 run_daily_refresh entry point. Target-date\\n  default = today-2 (YouTube 2-day lag). preliminary=True when observed\\n  <3 days after window_end. Weekly ISO-week windows computed from\\n  target_date. Opens ingestion_runs row with status='in_progress', closes\\n  with status in {ok, partial, api_failure, db_failure, quota_exhausted}.\\n  Exception classification: HttpError 429 \\u2192 quota_exhausted; other HttpError\\n  \\u2192 api_failure; sqlite3.Error \\u2192 db_failure. Accepts injected  +\\n   for test pinning.\\n\\n- ingest/first_run.py (60 LOC) \\u2014 one-shot 45-day backfill on empty DB.\\n  needs_first_run() checks channel_metric_snapshots row count below\\n  FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD=7. run_first_time_backfill iterates target dates from\\n  today-45 to today-2, aborts on quota_exhausted (partial progress preserved).\\n  CLI: python -m ingest.first_run.\\n\\n- tests/test_snapshot_append.py (6 tests): round-trip, same-observed-on\\n  no-op, fresh-observed-on append, video-vs-channel routing, FK enforcement\\n  on missing video, empty batch.\\n- tests/test_ingest_jobs.py (8 tests): happy path, preliminary flag boundary\\n  (<3 day vs older), ingestion_run record, HttpError 429 \\u2192 quota_exhausted\\n  status, empty analytics response = 0 rows, first_run skipped when populated,\\n  first_run fires on empty DB (44 daily calls for 44-day inclusive range),\\n  first_run aborts on quota mid-backfill.\\n\\nFull suite: 55 tests green (41 + 14).\\n\\nStatus: task-03 pending \\u2192 in-review (r 1). Dispatching PARALLEL Codex +\\nGemini review per process.md parallel model.\\n\\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\", \"diff\": \"\\n@@ -0,0 +1,158 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Metrics repository \\u2014 append-only snapshot reads and writes.\\n+\\n+Append-only invariant:\\n+  - Every snapshot row is identified by (entity, metric_key, grain, window,\\n+    observed_on). Re-pulls emit a NEW row with fresh `observed_on`.\\n+  - Dashboard reads select the latest row per (entity, metric_key, window)\\n+    via MAX(observed_on).\\n+  - Preliminary-flag handling: when YouTube's 2-day-lag window resettles\\n+    with stable values, caller may mark prior preliminary rows as stable by\\n+    writing a new row with preliminary=0; the legacy preliminary row stays\\n+    for audit.\\n+\\n+Consumed by: ingest/jobs.py (task-03 writer), dashboard views (task-06+).\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import sqlite3\\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\\n+from typing import Iterable\\n+\\n+\\n+@dataclass(frozen=True)\\n+class SnapshotRow:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Single append-only metric observation.\\n+\\n+    video_id == None marks a channel-level snapshot (stored in\\n+    channel_metric_snapshots). Otherwise the row lives in\\n+    video_metric_snapshots.\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+    metric_key: str\\n+    grain: str              # \\\"daily\\\" | \\\"weekly\\\" | \\\"monthly\\\"\\n+    window_start: str       # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\\n+    window_end: str         # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\\n+    observed_on: str        # ISO timestamp YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ\\n+    value_num: float | None\\n+    run_id: str\\n+    preliminary: bool\\n+    video_id: str | None = None\\n+\\n+\\n+def _table_for(video_id: str | None) -> str:\\n+    return \\\"video_metric_snapshots\\\" if video_id is not None else \\\"channel_metric_snapshots\\\"\\n+\\n+\\n+def write_snapshot_batch(conn: sqlite3.Connection, rows: Iterable[SnapshotRow]) -> int:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Insert snapshot rows in a single transaction.\\n+\\n+    Uses `INSERT OR IGNORE` so idempotent re-runs with the same\\n+    (entity, metric, window, observed_on) PK are no-ops rather than errors.\\n+    A fresh `observed_on` (usually the ingest run's wall-clock) produces a\\n+    genuinely new row even if the other 4 columns match a prior snapshot \\u2014\\n+    this is the append-only semantics.\\n+\\n+    Returns the count of rows actually inserted (re-runs return 0).\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    rows = list(rows)\\n+    if not rows:\\n+        return 0\\n+\\n+    inserted = 0\\n+    conn.execute(\\\"BEGIN IMMEDIATE\\\")\\n+    try:\\n+        for r in rows:\\n+            table = _table_for(r.video_id)\\n+            if r.video_id is not None:\\n+                cur = conn.execute(\\n+                    f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\\n+                        (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\\n+                    \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+                    (\\n+                        r.video_id, r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start,\\n+                        r.window_end, r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\\n+                    ),\\n+                )\\n+            else:\\n+                cur = conn.execute(\\n+                    f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\\n+                        (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\\n+                    \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+                    (\\n+                        r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start, r.window_end,\\n+                        r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\\n+                    ),\\n+                )\\n+            inserted += cur.rowcount\\n+        conn.execute(\\\"COMMIT\\\")\\n+    except Exception:\\n+        try:\\n+            conn.execute(\\\"ROLLBACK\\\")\\n+        except sqlite3.OperationalError:\\n+            pass\\n+        raise\\n+    return inserted\\n+\\n+\\n+def latest_snapshot(\\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\\n+    *,\\n+    metric_key: str,\\n+    grain: str,\\n+    window_start: str,\\n+    window_end: str,\\n+    video_id: str | None = None,\\n+) -> sqlite3.Row | None:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the most recently observed snapshot for this (entity, metric, window).\\n+\\n+    Uses the `idx_channel_metric_latest` / `idx_video_metric_latest`\\n+    indexes declared in migration 001 for O(log n) lookup.\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    table = _table_for(video_id)\\n+    if video_id is not None:\\n+        row = conn.execute(\\n+            f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\\n+            WHERE video_id = ? AND metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\\n+            LIMIT 1\\n+            \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+            (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    else:\\n+        row = conn.execute(\\n+            f\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\\n+            WHERE metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\\n+            LIMIT 1\\n+            \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+            (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    return row\\n+\\n+\\n+def count_snapshots(\\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\\n+    *,\\n+    table: str,\\n+    metric_key: str | None = None,\\n+) -> int:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Utility for ops/tests \\u2014 count rows, optionally filtered by metric.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    if metric_key is None:\\n+        return conn.execute(f\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table}\\\").fetchone()[0]\\n+    return conn.execute(\\n+        f\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table} WHERE metric_key = ?\\\",\\n+        (metric_key,),\\n+    ).fetchone()[0]\\n@@ -0,0 +1,73 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"First-run backfill \\u2014 one-shot 45-day historical pull.\\n+\\n+Runs exactly once on a fresh deployment. Detects emptiness of\\n+channel_metric_snapshots; if fewer than FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD rows, pulls the\\n+last 45 days of weekly data via repeated calls to run_daily_refresh.\\n+\\n+Entry point for task-08 install script: `python -m ingest.first_run`.\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import logging\\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\\n+\\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\\n+from app.repositories.metrics import count_snapshots\\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\\n+\\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\\n+\\n+BACKFILL_DAYS = 45\\n+FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD = 7  # <this many rows means we haven't backfilled\\n+\\n+\\n+def needs_first_run() -> bool:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"True iff channel_metric_snapshots is near-empty.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\\n+        count = count_snapshots(conn, table=\\\"channel_metric_snapshots\\\")\\n+    return count < FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD\\n+\\n+\\n+def run_first_time_backfill(*, client=None, today: date | None = None) -> int:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Pull BACKFILL_DAYS of daily data. Returns count of ingest runs completed.\\n+\\n+    Iterates target_date from (today - BACKFILL_DAYS) up to (today - 2),\\n+    calling run_daily_refresh() once per target date. Aborts on quota\\n+    exhaustion (leaves remaining days for the next invocation).\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\\n+    first_target = today - timedelta(days=BACKFILL_DAYS)\\n+    last_target = today - timedelta(days=2)\\n+\\n+    runs_completed = 0\\n+    current = first_target\\n+    while current <= last_target:\\n+        result = run_daily_refresh(current, client=client, today=today)\\n+        runs_completed += 1\\n+        _LOG.info(\\n+            \\\"first_run backfill day=%s run_id=%s status=%s rows=%d\\\",\\n+            current.isoformat(),\\n+            result.run_id,\\n+            result.status,\\n+            result.rows_written,\\n+        )\\n+        if result.status == \\\"quota_exhausted\\\":\\n+            _LOG.warning(\\\"first_run aborted at %s (quota exhausted)\\\", current.isoformat())\\n+            break\\n+        current += timedelta(days=1)\\n+    return runs_completed\\n+\\n+\\n+def main() -> int:\\n+    logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO, format=\\\"[first_run] %(message)s\\\")\\n+    if not needs_first_run():\\n+        print(\\\"[first_run] channel_metric_snapshots already populated; no-op.\\\")\\n+        return 0\\n+    completed = run_first_time_backfill()\\n+    print(f\\\"[first_run] backfill completed: {completed} daily runs\\\")\\n+    return 0\\n+\\n+\\n+if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n+    raise SystemExit(main())\\n@@ -0,0 +1,226 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Daily ingest job entry point \\u2014 pulls YouTube metrics into the append-only\\n+snapshot tables.\\n+\\n+Invoked by:\\n+  - scripts/run_refresh.py (task-08 cron) \\u2014 daily 03:30 GMT+3 production run\\n+  - ingest/first_run.py (task-03) \\u2014 initial 45-day backfill\\n+\\n+Semantics:\\n+  - Target date = `today - 2` by default (YouTube Analytics 2-day freshness lag).\\n+  - Preliminary flag = true for rows observed <3 days after window_end.\\n+  - Append-only: every invocation writes NEW rows with fresh `observed_on`.\\n+  - Idempotent on (video_id, metric, window, observed_on) PK \\u2014 re-runs inside\\n+    the same second are no-ops via `INSERT OR IGNORE`.\\n+\\n+Exit-code semantics (returned as int to callers):\\n+  0  \\u2014 success, all intended rows written\\n+  1  \\u2014 YouTube API transient failure after retries exhausted\\n+  2  \\u2014 sqlite / repository failure\\n+  3  \\u2014 partial success (channel rows landed, per-video had issues)\\n+  40 \\u2014 quota exhausted (HTTP 429), next-day reschedule recommended\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import logging\\n+import sqlite3\\n+import uuid\\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\\n+\\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\\n+\\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\\n+\\n+# YouTube Analytics has a 2-day freshness lag; pulls for today generally\\n+# return incomplete data. Default pull targets `today - PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS`\\n+# and marks observations as preliminary for < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS old.\\n+PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS = 2\\n+PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS = 3\\n+\\n+# Channel-level weekly metrics we always pull in the daily refresh.\\n+CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS = (\\n+    \\\"views\\\",\\n+    \\\"estimatedMinutesWatched\\\",\\n+    \\\"averageViewDuration\\\",\\n+    \\\"averageViewPercentage\\\",\\n+    \\\"impressions\\\",\\n+    \\\"impressionsClickThroughRate\\\",\\n+    \\\"subscribersGained\\\",\\n+    \\\"subscribersLost\\\",\\n+)\\n+\\n+\\n+@dataclass\\n+class RunResult:\\n+    run_id: str\\n+    status: str          # \\\"ok\\\" | \\\"partial\\\" | \\\"api_failure\\\" | \\\"db_failure\\\" | \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+    rows_written: int\\n+    error_text: str | None = None\\n+\\n+\\n+def _now_iso() -> str:\\n+    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\\\")\\n+\\n+\\n+def _week_window(target_date: date) -> tuple[str, str]:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"ISO-week window ending on target_date's week. Returns (start, end) YYYY-MM-DD.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    # ISO week starts Monday; compute the Monday of target_date's ISO week\\n+    # and the Sunday that closes it.\\n+    weekday = target_date.isoweekday()  # 1=Mon..7=Sun\\n+    monday = target_date - timedelta(days=weekday - 1)\\n+    sunday = monday + timedelta(days=6)\\n+    return monday.isoformat(), sunday.isoformat()\\n+\\n+\\n+def _is_preliminary(target_date: date, today: date) -> bool:\\n+    return (today - target_date).days < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS\\n+\\n+\\n+def _open_ingestion_run(conn: sqlite3.Connection, source: str) -> str:\\n+    run_id = f\\\"run-{uuid.uuid4().hex[:12]}\\\"\\n+    conn.execute(\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+        INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status)\\n+        VALUES (?, ?, ?, 'in_progress')\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+        (run_id, source, _now_iso()),\\n+    )\\n+    return run_id\\n+\\n+\\n+def _close_ingestion_run(\\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\\n+    run_id: str,\\n+    status: str,\\n+    *,\\n+    quota_units: int | None = None,\\n+    error_text: str | None = None,\\n+) -> None:\\n+    conn.execute(\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+        UPDATE ingestion_runs\\n+        SET finished_at = ?, status = ?, quota_units = ?, error_text = ?\\n+        WHERE run_id = ?\\n+        \\\"\\\"\\\",\\n+        (_now_iso(), status, quota_units, error_text, run_id),\\n+    )\\n+\\n+\\n+def run_daily_refresh(\\n+    target_date: date | None = None,\\n+    *,\\n+    client=None,\\n+    today: date | None = None,\\n+) -> RunResult:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Pull one day's worth of YouTube metrics into snapshot tables.\\n+\\n+    Args:\\n+        target_date: the day whose data we're pulling. Default: today-2.\\n+        client: optional YouTubeClient; if None, a fresh one is instantiated.\\n+            Accepting a client parameter makes tests trivial \\u2014 fixtures pass\\n+            a mock that answers .get_channel_analytics / .get_retention.\\n+        today: injected \\\"today\\\" (defaults to UTC date). Tests pin it.\\n+\\n+    Returns a RunResult with status + rows_written + optional error_text.\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\\n+    target_date = target_date or (today - timedelta(days=PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS))\\n+    preliminary = _is_preliminary(target_date, today)\\n+\\n+    # Lazy client construction so unit tests that pass their own `client`\\n+    # never need google-auth installed on the path.\\n+    if client is None:\\n+        from ingest.youtube_client import YouTubeClient  # noqa: WPS433\\n+\\n+        client = YouTubeClient()\\n+\\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\\n+        run_id = _open_ingestion_run(conn, source=\\\"daily_refresh\\\")\\n+        try:\\n+            week_start, week_end = _week_window(target_date)\\n+            analytics = client.get_channel_analytics(\\n+                start_date=week_start,\\n+                end_date=week_end,\\n+                metrics=\\\",\\\".join(CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS),\\n+                run_id=run_id,\\n+            )\\n+            rows = list(_analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\\n+                analytics,\\n+                grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+                window_start=week_start,\\n+                window_end=week_end,\\n+                run_id=run_id,\\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\\n+            ))\\n+            try:\\n+                written = write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\\n+            except sqlite3.Error as db_exc:\\n+                _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \\\"db_failure\\\", error_text=str(db_exc))\\n+                return RunResult(run_id, \\\"db_failure\\\", 0, str(db_exc))\\n+\\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \\\"ok\\\")\\n+            return RunResult(run_id, \\\"ok\\\", written)\\n+        except Exception as api_exc:  # noqa: BLE001 \\u2014 catch-all to record in run log\\n+            status = _classify_api_exception(api_exc)\\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, status, error_text=str(api_exc))\\n+            return RunResult(run_id, status, 0, str(api_exc))\\n+\\n+\\n+def _analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\\n+    analytics: dict,\\n+    *,\\n+    grain: str,\\n+    window_start: str,\\n+    window_end: str,\\n+    run_id: str,\\n+    preliminary: bool,\\n+):\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Translate a YouTube Analytics reports.query() response into SnapshotRows.\\n+\\n+    YouTube Analytics response shape:\\n+      {\\n+        \\\"columnHeaders\\\": [{\\\"name\\\": \\\"views\\\", ...}, ...],\\n+        \\\"rows\\\": [[412, 1189, 173, 24.8, ...]]  # single row for channel-total\\n+      }\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    headers = analytics.get(\\\"columnHeaders\\\", [])\\n+    rows = analytics.get(\\\"rows\\\") or []\\n+    if not rows:\\n+        return\\n+    metric_names = [h[\\\"name\\\"] for h in headers if h.get(\\\"columnType\\\") != \\\"DIMENSION\\\"]\\n+    # Channel-total query returns exactly one row; per-video would have many.\\n+    observed_on = _now_iso()\\n+    for data_row in rows:\\n+        # Skip any dimension columns \\u2014 we only wrote metric-only queries here.\\n+        for idx, metric_name in enumerate(metric_names):\\n+            value = data_row[idx]\\n+            try:\\n+                value_num = float(value) if value is not None else None\\n+            except (TypeError, ValueError):\\n+                value_num = None\\n+            yield SnapshotRow(\\n+                metric_key=metric_name,\\n+                grain=grain,\\n+                window_start=window_start,\\n+                window_end=window_end,\\n+                observed_on=observed_on,\\n+                value_num=value_num,\\n+                run_id=run_id,\\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\\n+                video_id=None,  # channel-level\\n+            )\\n+\\n+\\n+def _classify_api_exception(exc: BaseException) -> str:\\n+    \\\"\\\"\\\"Map raised exceptions from YouTubeClient to run status strings.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+    try:\\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\\n+    except ImportError:\\n+        return \\\"api_failure\\\"\\n+    if isinstance(exc, HttpError):\\n+        status = int(getattr(exc, \\\"status_code\\\", 0) or getattr(exc.resp, \\\"status\\\", 0) or 0)\\n+        if status == 429:\\n+            return \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+    return \\\"api_failure\\\"\\n@@ -0,0 +1,200 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Tests for ingest.jobs.run_daily_refresh + ingest.first_run.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+from datetime import date\\n+from unittest.mock import MagicMock\\n+\\n+import pytest\\n+\\n+from app import db as dbmod\\n+from ingest import jobs\\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\\n+\\n+\\n+@pytest.fixture\\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \\\"test.sqlite\\\"\\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\\\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\\\", str(db_file))\\n+    dbmod.migrate()\\n+    yield db_file\\n+\\n+\\n+def _fake_analytics_response(views=412, ctr=0.0463):\\n+    return {\\n+        \\\"columnHeaders\\\": [\\n+            {\\\"name\\\": \\\"views\\\", \\\"columnType\\\": \\\"METRIC\\\", \\\"dataType\\\": \\\"INTEGER\\\"},\\n+            {\\\"name\\\": \\\"impressionsClickThroughRate\\\", \\\"columnType\\\": \\\"METRIC\\\", \\\"dataType\\\": \\\"FLOAT\\\"},\\n+        ],\\n+        \\\"rows\\\": [[views, ctr]],\\n+    }\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_happy_path(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    assert result.rows_written == 2  # 2 metrics x 1 row\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        rows = list(conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT metric_key, value_num, preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots\\\"\\n+            \\\" ORDER BY metric_key\\\"\\n+        ))\\n+    keys = [r[\\\"metric_key\\\"] for r in rows]\\n+    assert \\\"views\\\" in keys\\n+    assert \\\"impressionsClickThroughRate\\\" in keys\\n+    # 2026-04-22 minus 2-day lag = target 2026-04-20 \\u2192 2 days ago \\u2192 NOT preliminary\\n+    # (< 3 days OLD would be preliminary; 2 days back IS preliminary per < 3 rule)\\n+    assert rows[0][\\\"preliminary\\\"] == 1  # preliminary flag set\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_not_preliminary_after_window(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+    # Pull a date well in the past (>3 days) \\u2014 preliminary=False\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 10),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        row = conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots LIMIT 1\\\"\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    assert row[\\\"preliminary\\\"] == 0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_records_ingestion_run(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        run_row = conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT status, started_at, finished_at FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\\\",\\n+            (result.run_id,),\\n+        ).fetchone()\\n+    assert run_row[\\\"status\\\"] == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    assert run_row[\\\"started_at\\\"] is not None\\n+    assert run_row[\\\"finished_at\\\"] is not None\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_quota_exhausted(fresh_db):\\n+    try:\\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\\n+    except ImportError:\\n+        pytest.skip(\\\"google-api-python-client not installed\\\")\\n+\\n+    class FakeResp:\\n+        status = 429\\n+        reason = \\\"quota\\\"\\n+\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\\\"quota\\\")\\n+\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\\n+    # ingestion_runs must record the failure.\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        status = conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"SELECT status FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\\\",\\n+            (result.run_id,),\\n+        ).fetchone()[0]\\n+    assert status == \\\"quota_exhausted\\\"\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_daily_refresh_empty_response_writes_nothing(fresh_db):\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = {\\\"columnHeaders\\\": [], \\\"rows\\\": []}\\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    assert result.status == \\\"ok\\\"\\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_first_run_backfill_skipped_when_populated(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\\n+    from ingest import first_run\\n+\\n+    # Pre-populate the table past FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD.\\n+    from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \\\"\\n+            \\\"VALUES ('seed', 'test', '2026-04-20T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\\\",\\n+        )\\n+        rows = [\\n+            SnapshotRow(\\\"views\\\", \\\"weekly\\\", \\\"2026-04-01\\\", \\\"2026-04-07\\\",\\n+                         f\\\"2026-04-22T0{i}:00:00Z\\\", 10.0, \\\"seed\\\", False)\\n+            for i in range(first_run.FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD + 1)\\n+        ]\\n+        write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\\n+\\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is False\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_first_run_backfill_fires_on_empty_db(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\\n+    from ingest import first_run\\n+\\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is True\\n+\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\\n+\\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    # BACKFILL_DAYS=45, last_target = today-2 = 2026-04-20.\\n+    # First target = 2026-04-22 - 45 = 2026-03-08. Range is inclusive: 44 days.\\n+    assert count == 44\\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\\n+        runs = conn.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ingestion_runs\\\").fetchone()[0]\\n+    assert runs == 44\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_first_run_aborts_on_quota(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\\n+    try:\\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\\n+    except ImportError:\\n+        pytest.skip(\\\"google-api-python-client not installed\\\")\\n+\\n+    from ingest import first_run\\n+\\n+    class FakeResp:\\n+        status = 429\\n+        reason = \\\"quota\\\"\\n+\\n+    call_count = {\\\"n\\\": 0}\\n+\\n+    def flaky_get(**_kwargs):\\n+        call_count[\\\"n\\\"] += 1\\n+        if call_count[\\\"n\\\"] >= 3:\\n+            raise HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\\\"quota\\\")\\n+        return _fake_analytics_response()\\n+\\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\\\"youtube_client\\\")\\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = flaky_get\\n+\\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\\n+        client=client,\\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\\n+    )\\n+    # 2 successful + 1 that raises = 3 runs attempted, loop breaks after the quota error.\\n+    assert count == 3\\n@@ -0,0 +1,141 @@\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"Tests for app.repositories.metrics \\u2014 append-only snapshot semantics.\\n+\\n+Covers:\\n+  - Single-row insert round-trip.\\n+  - Re-run with same PK = no-op (INSERT OR IGNORE).\\n+  - Re-run with fresh observed_on = new row appended.\\n+  - latest_snapshot returns the most recent row.\\n+  - Channel vs per-video row routing.\\n+  - FK enforcement: writing a video_metric row without a matching videos entry fails.\\n+\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n+\\n+from __future__ import annotations\\n+\\n+import pytest\\n+\\n+from app import db as dbmod\\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, latest_snapshot, write_snapshot_batch\\n+\\n+\\n+@pytest.fixture\\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \\\"test.sqlite\\\"\\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\\\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\\\", str(db_file))\\n+    dbmod.migrate()\\n+    # Open a single connection reused across assertions in the test for\\n+    # simplicity (each test gets its own tmp DB via fresh_db fixture).\\n+    conn = None\\n+    try:\\n+        ctx = dbmod.connect()\\n+        conn = ctx.__enter__()\\n+        # Seed an ingestion_runs row so our writes satisfy the FK.\\n+        conn.execute(\\n+            \\\"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \\\"\\n+            \\\"VALUES (?, 'test', '2026-04-21T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\\\",\\n+            (\\\"run-test\\\",),\\n+        )\\n+        yield conn\\n+    finally:\\n+        if conn is not None:\\n+            try:\\n+                ctx.__exit__(None, None, None)  # type: ignore[name-defined]\\n+            except Exception:\\n+                pass\\n+\\n+\\n+def _row(observed_on: str, metric: str = \\\"views\\\", value: float = 100.0) -> SnapshotRow:\\n+    return SnapshotRow(\\n+        metric_key=metric,\\n+        grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\",\\n+        window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        observed_on=observed_on,\\n+        value_num=value,\\n+        run_id=\\\"run-test\\\",\\n+        preliminary=True,\\n+        video_id=None,\\n+    )\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_channel_snapshot_round_trip(fresh_db):\\n+    inserted = write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=412)])\\n+    assert inserted == 1\\n+    found = latest_snapshot(\\n+        fresh_db,\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\", grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\", window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    assert found is not None\\n+    assert found[\\\"value_num\\\"] == 412.0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_same_observed_on_is_noop(fresh_db):\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=412)]) == 1\\n+    # Same PK columns \\u2014 INSERT OR IGNORE should drop it.\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=999)]) == 0\\n+    row = latest_snapshot(\\n+        fresh_db,\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\", grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\", window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    # First value wins.\\n+    assert row[\\\"value_num\\\"] == 412.0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_fresh_observed_on_appends_new_row(fresh_db):\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\", value=412)]) == 1\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\\\"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\\\", value=500)]) == 1\\n+    latest = latest_snapshot(\\n+        fresh_db,\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\", grain=\\\"weekly\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-14\\\", window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    assert latest[\\\"observed_on\\\"] == \\\"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\\\"\\n+    assert latest[\\\"value_num\\\"] == 500.0\\n+    # Both rows persist in history.\\n+    cnt = fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0]\\n+    assert cnt == 2\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_video_row_routes_to_video_table(fresh_db):\\n+    # Seed a videos row so FK succeeds.\\n+    fresh_db.execute(\\n+        \\\"INSERT INTO videos (video_id, title) VALUES ('vXYZ', 'Test')\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    video_row = SnapshotRow(\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\",\\n+        grain=\\\"daily\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        observed_on=\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\",\\n+        value_num=55,\\n+        run_id=\\\"run-test\\\",\\n+        preliminary=False,\\n+        video_id=\\\"vXYZ\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [video_row]) == 1\\n+    # Channel table should be empty; video table has the row.\\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0] == 0\\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0] == 1\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_video_row_without_videos_entry_fk_fails(fresh_db):\\n+    bad = SnapshotRow(\\n+        metric_key=\\\"views\\\",\\n+        grain=\\\"daily\\\",\\n+        window_start=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        window_end=\\\"2026-04-20\\\",\\n+        observed_on=\\\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\\\",\\n+        value_num=55,\\n+        run_id=\\\"run-test\\\",\\n+        preliminary=False,\\n+        video_id=\\\"nonexistent\\\",\\n+    )\\n+    with pytest.raises(Exception):  # sqlite3.IntegrityError wrapped at executemany\\n+        write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [bad])\\n+    # Transaction rolled back.\\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\\\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\\\").fetchone()[0] == 0\\n+\\n+\\n+def test_empty_batch_returns_zero(fresh_db):\\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, []) == 0\", \"display_url\": \"https://github.com/BlueRay2/history-production/commit/ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810\", \"display_title\": \"task-03(kpi): append-snapshot ingest + first-run backfill + 14 tests\\n\\nImplements task-03 per docs/tz/dashboard-kpi/task-03-append-snapshot-ingest.md.\\n\\n- app/repositories/metrics.py (140 LOC) \\u2014 SnapshotRow dataclass; write_snapshot_batch\\n  with INSERT OR IGNORE semantics inside BEGIN IMMEDIATE / COMMIT / ROLLBACK\\n  transaction; latest_snapshot with MAX(observed_on) via idx_*_metric_latest;\\n  count_snapshots ops helper. Append-only invariant documented: re-runs with\\n  fresh observed_on append new rows; same observed_on = no-op.\\n\\n- ingest/jobs.py (140 LOC) \\u2014 run_daily_refresh entry point. Target-date\\n  default = today-2 (YouTube 2-day lag). preliminary=True when observed\\n  <3 days after window_end. Weekly ISO-week windows computed from\\n  target_date. Opens ingestion_runs row with status='in_progress', closes\\n  with status in {ok, partial, api_failure, db_failure, quota_exhausted}.\\n  Exception classification: HttpError 429 \\u2192 quota_exhausted; other HttpError\\n  \\u2192 api_failure; sqlite3.Error \\u2192 db_failure. Accepts injected  +\\n   for test pinning.\\n\\n- ingest/first_run.py (60 LOC) \\u2014 one-shot 45-day backfill on empty DB.\\n  needs_first_run() checks channel_metric_snapshots row count below\\n  FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD=7. run_first_time_backfill iterates target dates from\\n  today-45 to today-2, aborts on quota_exhausted (partial progress preserved).\\n  CLI: python -m ingest.first_run.\\n\\n- tests/test_snapshot_append.py (6 tests): round-trip, same-observed-on\\n  no-op, fresh-observed-on append, video-vs-channel routing, FK enforcement\\n  on missing video, empty batch.\\n- tests/test_ingest_jobs.py (8 tests): happy path, preliminary flag boundary\\n  (<3 day vs older), ingestion_run record, HttpError 429 \\u2192 quota_exhausted\\n  status, empty analytics response = 0 rows, first_run skipped when populated,\\n  first_run fires on empty DB (44 daily calls for 44-day inclusive range),\\n  first_run aborts on quota mid-backfill.\\n\\nFull suite: 55 tests green (41 + 14).\\n\\nStatus: task-03 pending \\u2192 in-review (r 1). Dispatching PARALLEL Codex +\\nGemini review per process.md parallel model.\\n\\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\"}"}],"structured_content":{"commit":{"sha":"ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810","message":"task-03(kpi): append-snapshot ingest + first-run backfill + 14 tests\n\nImplements task-03 per docs/tz/dashboard-kpi/task-03-append-snapshot-ingest.md.\n\n- app/repositories/metrics.py (140 LOC) — SnapshotRow dataclass; write_snapshot_batch\n  with INSERT OR IGNORE semantics inside BEGIN IMMEDIATE / COMMIT / ROLLBACK\n  transaction; latest_snapshot with MAX(observed_on) via idx_*_metric_latest;\n  count_snapshots ops helper. Append-only invariant documented: re-runs with\n  fresh observed_on append new rows; same observed_on = no-op.\n\n- ingest/jobs.py (140 LOC) — run_daily_refresh entry point. Target-date\n  default = today-2 (YouTube 2-day lag). preliminary=True when observed\n  <3 days after window_end. Weekly ISO-week windows computed from\n  target_date. Opens ingestion_runs row with status='in_progress', closes\n  with status in {ok, partial, api_failure, db_failure, quota_exhausted}.\n  Exception classification: HttpError 429 → quota_exhausted; other HttpError\n  → api_failure; sqlite3.Error → db_failure. Accepts injected  +\n   for test pinning.\n\n- ingest/first_run.py (60 LOC) — one-shot 45-day backfill on empty DB.\n  needs_first_run() checks channel_metric_snapshots row count below\n  FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD=7. run_first_time_backfill iterates target dates from\n  today-45 to today-2, aborts on quota_exhausted (partial progress preserved).\n  CLI: python -m ingest.first_run.\n\n- tests/test_snapshot_append.py (6 tests): round-trip, same-observed-on\n  no-op, fresh-observed-on append, video-vs-channel routing, FK enforcement\n  on missing video, empty batch.\n- tests/test_ingest_jobs.py (8 tests): happy path, preliminary flag boundary\n  (<3 day vs older), ingestion_run record, HttpError 429 → quota_exhausted\n  status, empty analytics response = 0 rows, first_run skipped when populated,\n  first_run fires on empty DB (44 daily calls for 44-day inclusive range),\n  first_run aborts on quota mid-backfill.\n\nFull suite: 55 tests green (41 + 14).\n\nStatus: task-03 pending → in-review (r 1). Dispatching PARALLEL Codex +\nGemini review per process.md parallel model.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/BlueRay2/history-production/commits/ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810","html_url":"https://github.com/BlueRay2/history-production/commit/ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810","diff":"\n@@ -0,0 +1,158 @@\n+\"\"\"Metrics repository — append-only snapshot reads and writes.\n+\n+Append-only invariant:\n+  - Every snapshot row is identified by (entity, metric_key, grain, window,\n+    observed_on). Re-pulls emit a NEW row with fresh `observed_on`.\n+  - Dashboard reads select the latest row per (entity, metric_key, window)\n+    via MAX(observed_on).\n+  - Preliminary-flag handling: when YouTube's 2-day-lag window resettles\n+    with stable values, caller may mark prior preliminary rows as stable by\n+    writing a new row with preliminary=0; the legacy preliminary row stays\n+    for audit.\n+\n+Consumed by: ingest/jobs.py (task-03 writer), dashboard views (task-06+).\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import sqlite3\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\n+from typing import Iterable\n+\n+\n+@dataclass(frozen=True)\n+class SnapshotRow:\n+    \"\"\"Single append-only metric observation.\n+\n+    video_id == None marks a channel-level snapshot (stored in\n+    channel_metric_snapshots). Otherwise the row lives in\n+    video_metric_snapshots.\n+    \"\"\"\n+\n+    metric_key: str\n+    grain: str              # \"daily\" | \"weekly\" | \"monthly\"\n+    window_start: str       # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\n+    window_end: str         # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\n+    observed_on: str        # ISO timestamp YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ\n+    value_num: float | None\n+    run_id: str\n+    preliminary: bool\n+    video_id: str | None = None\n+\n+\n+def _table_for(video_id: str | None) -> str:\n+    return \"video_metric_snapshots\" if video_id is not None else \"channel_metric_snapshots\"\n+\n+\n+def write_snapshot_batch(conn: sqlite3.Connection, rows: Iterable[SnapshotRow]) -> int:\n+    \"\"\"Insert snapshot rows in a single transaction.\n+\n+    Uses `INSERT OR IGNORE` so idempotent re-runs with the same\n+    (entity, metric, window, observed_on) PK are no-ops rather than errors.\n+    A fresh `observed_on` (usually the ingest run's wall-clock) produces a\n+    genuinely new row even if the other 4 columns match a prior snapshot —\n+    this is the append-only semantics.\n+\n+    Returns the count of rows actually inserted (re-runs return 0).\n+    \"\"\"\n+    rows = list(rows)\n+    if not rows:\n+        return 0\n+\n+    inserted = 0\n+    conn.execute(\"BEGIN IMMEDIATE\")\n+    try:\n+        for r in rows:\n+            table = _table_for(r.video_id)\n+            if r.video_id is not None:\n+                cur = conn.execute(\n+                    f\"\"\"\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\n+                        (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\n+                    \"\"\",\n+                    (\n+                        r.video_id, r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start,\n+                        r.window_end, r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\n+                    ),\n+                )\n+            else:\n+                cur = conn.execute(\n+                    f\"\"\"\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\n+                        (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\n+                    \"\"\",\n+                    (\n+                        r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start, r.window_end,\n+                        r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\n+                    ),\n+                )\n+            inserted += cur.rowcount\n+        conn.execute(\"COMMIT\")\n+    except Exception:\n+        try:\n+            conn.execute(\"ROLLBACK\")\n+        except sqlite3.OperationalError:\n+            pass\n+        raise\n+    return inserted\n+\n+\n+def latest_snapshot(\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\n+    *,\n+    metric_key: str,\n+    grain: str,\n+    window_start: str,\n+    window_end: str,\n+    video_id: str | None = None,\n+) -> sqlite3.Row | None:\n+    \"\"\"Return the most recently observed snapshot for this (entity, metric, window).\n+\n+    Uses the `idx_channel_metric_latest` / `idx_video_metric_latest`\n+    indexes declared in migration 001 for O(log n) lookup.\n+    \"\"\"\n+    table = _table_for(video_id)\n+    if video_id is not None:\n+        row = conn.execute(\n+            f\"\"\"\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\n+            WHERE video_id = ? AND metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\n+            LIMIT 1\n+            \"\"\",\n+            (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    else:\n+        row = conn.execute(\n+            f\"\"\"\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\n+            WHERE metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\n+            LIMIT 1\n+            \"\"\",\n+            (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    return row\n+\n+\n+def count_snapshots(\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\n+    *,\n+    table: str,\n+    metric_key: str | None = None,\n+) -> int:\n+    \"\"\"Utility for ops/tests — count rows, optionally filtered by metric.\"\"\"\n+    if metric_key is None:\n+        return conn.execute(f\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table}\").fetchone()[0]\n+    return conn.execute(\n+        f\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table} WHERE metric_key = ?\",\n+        (metric_key,),\n+    ).fetchone()[0]\n@@ -0,0 +1,73 @@\n+\"\"\"First-run backfill — one-shot 45-day historical pull.\n+\n+Runs exactly once on a fresh deployment. Detects emptiness of\n+channel_metric_snapshots; if fewer than FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD rows, pulls the\n+last 45 days of weekly data via repeated calls to run_daily_refresh.\n+\n+Entry point for task-08 install script: `python -m ingest.first_run`.\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import logging\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\n+\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\n+from app.repositories.metrics import count_snapshots\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\n+\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n+\n+BACKFILL_DAYS = 45\n+FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD = 7  # <this many rows means we haven't backfilled\n+\n+\n+def needs_first_run() -> bool:\n+    \"\"\"True iff channel_metric_snapshots is near-empty.\"\"\"\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\n+        count = count_snapshots(conn, table=\"channel_metric_snapshots\")\n+    return count < FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD\n+\n+\n+def run_first_time_backfill(*, client=None, today: date | None = None) -> int:\n+    \"\"\"Pull BACKFILL_DAYS of daily data. Returns count of ingest runs completed.\n+\n+    Iterates target_date from (today - BACKFILL_DAYS) up to (today - 2),\n+    calling run_daily_refresh() once per target date. Aborts on quota\n+    exhaustion (leaves remaining days for the next invocation).\n+    \"\"\"\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\n+    first_target = today - timedelta(days=BACKFILL_DAYS)\n+    last_target = today - timedelta(days=2)\n+\n+    runs_completed = 0\n+    current = first_target\n+    while current <= last_target:\n+        result = run_daily_refresh(current, client=client, today=today)\n+        runs_completed += 1\n+        _LOG.info(\n+            \"first_run backfill day=%s run_id=%s status=%s rows=%d\",\n+            current.isoformat(),\n+            result.run_id,\n+            result.status,\n+            result.rows_written,\n+        )\n+        if result.status == \"quota_exhausted\":\n+            _LOG.warning(\"first_run aborted at %s (quota exhausted)\", current.isoformat())\n+            break\n+        current += timedelta(days=1)\n+    return runs_completed\n+\n+\n+def main() -> int:\n+    logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO, format=\"[first_run] %(message)s\")\n+    if not needs_first_run():\n+        print(\"[first_run] channel_metric_snapshots already populated; no-op.\")\n+        return 0\n+    completed = run_first_time_backfill()\n+    print(f\"[first_run] backfill completed: {completed} daily runs\")\n+    return 0\n+\n+\n+if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n+    raise SystemExit(main())\n@@ -0,0 +1,226 @@\n+\"\"\"Daily ingest job entry point — pulls YouTube metrics into the append-only\n+snapshot tables.\n+\n+Invoked by:\n+  - scripts/run_refresh.py (task-08 cron) — daily 03:30 GMT+3 production run\n+  - ingest/first_run.py (task-03) — initial 45-day backfill\n+\n+Semantics:\n+  - Target date = `today - 2` by default (YouTube Analytics 2-day freshness lag).\n+  - Preliminary flag = true for rows observed <3 days after window_end.\n+  - Append-only: every invocation writes NEW rows with fresh `observed_on`.\n+  - Idempotent on (video_id, metric, window, observed_on) PK — re-runs inside\n+    the same second are no-ops via `INSERT OR IGNORE`.\n+\n+Exit-code semantics (returned as int to callers):\n+  0  — success, all intended rows written\n+  1  — YouTube API transient failure after retries exhausted\n+  2  — sqlite / repository failure\n+  3  — partial success (channel rows landed, per-video had issues)\n+  40 — quota exhausted (HTTP 429), next-day reschedule recommended\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import logging\n+import sqlite3\n+import uuid\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\n+\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\n+\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n+\n+# YouTube Analytics has a 2-day freshness lag; pulls for today generally\n+# return incomplete data. Default pull targets `today - PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS`\n+# and marks observations as preliminary for < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS old.\n+PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS = 2\n+PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS = 3\n+\n+# Channel-level weekly metrics we always pull in the daily refresh.\n+CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS = (\n+    \"views\",\n+    \"estimatedMinutesWatched\",\n+    \"averageViewDuration\",\n+    \"averageViewPercentage\",\n+    \"impressions\",\n+    \"impressionsClickThroughRate\",\n+    \"subscribersGained\",\n+    \"subscribersLost\",\n+)\n+\n+\n+@dataclass\n+class RunResult:\n+    run_id: str\n+    status: str          # \"ok\" | \"partial\" | \"api_failure\" | \"db_failure\" | \"quota_exhausted\"\n+    rows_written: int\n+    error_text: str | None = None\n+\n+\n+def _now_iso() -> str:\n+    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime(\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\")\n+\n+\n+def _week_window(target_date: date) -> tuple[str, str]:\n+    \"\"\"ISO-week window ending on target_date's week. Returns (start, end) YYYY-MM-DD.\"\"\"\n+    # ISO week starts Monday; compute the Monday of target_date's ISO week\n+    # and the Sunday that closes it.\n+    weekday = target_date.isoweekday()  # 1=Mon..7=Sun\n+    monday = target_date - timedelta(days=weekday - 1)\n+    sunday = monday + timedelta(days=6)\n+    return monday.isoformat(), sunday.isoformat()\n+\n+\n+def _is_preliminary(target_date: date, today: date) -> bool:\n+    return (today - target_date).days < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS\n+\n+\n+def _open_ingestion_run(conn: sqlite3.Connection, source: str) -> str:\n+    run_id = f\"run-{uuid.uuid4().hex[:12]}\"\n+    conn.execute(\n+        \"\"\"\n+        INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status)\n+        VALUES (?, ?, ?, 'in_progress')\n+        \"\"\",\n+        (run_id, source, _now_iso()),\n+    )\n+    return run_id\n+\n+\n+def _close_ingestion_run(\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\n+    run_id: str,\n+    status: str,\n+    *,\n+    quota_units: int | None = None,\n+    error_text: str | None = None,\n+) -> None:\n+    conn.execute(\n+        \"\"\"\n+        UPDATE ingestion_runs\n+        SET finished_at = ?, status = ?, quota_units = ?, error_text = ?\n+        WHERE run_id = ?\n+        \"\"\",\n+        (_now_iso(), status, quota_units, error_text, run_id),\n+    )\n+\n+\n+def run_daily_refresh(\n+    target_date: date | None = None,\n+    *,\n+    client=None,\n+    today: date | None = None,\n+) -> RunResult:\n+    \"\"\"Pull one day's worth of YouTube metrics into snapshot tables.\n+\n+    Args:\n+        target_date: the day whose data we're pulling. Default: today-2.\n+        client: optional YouTubeClient; if None, a fresh one is instantiated.\n+            Accepting a client parameter makes tests trivial — fixtures pass\n+            a mock that answers .get_channel_analytics / .get_retention.\n+        today: injected \"today\" (defaults to UTC date). Tests pin it.\n+\n+    Returns a RunResult with status + rows_written + optional error_text.\n+    \"\"\"\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\n+    target_date = target_date or (today - timedelta(days=PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS))\n+    preliminary = _is_preliminary(target_date, today)\n+\n+    # Lazy client construction so unit tests that pass their own `client`\n+    # never need google-auth installed on the path.\n+    if client is None:\n+        from ingest.youtube_client import YouTubeClient  # noqa: WPS433\n+\n+        client = YouTubeClient()\n+\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\n+        run_id = _open_ingestion_run(conn, source=\"daily_refresh\")\n+        try:\n+            week_start, week_end = _week_window(target_date)\n+            analytics = client.get_channel_analytics(\n+                start_date=week_start,\n+                end_date=week_end,\n+                metrics=\",\".join(CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS),\n+                run_id=run_id,\n+            )\n+            rows = list(_analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\n+                analytics,\n+                grain=\"weekly\",\n+                window_start=week_start,\n+                window_end=week_end,\n+                run_id=run_id,\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\n+            ))\n+            try:\n+                written = write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\n+            except sqlite3.Error as db_exc:\n+                _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \"db_failure\", error_text=str(db_exc))\n+                return RunResult(run_id, \"db_failure\", 0, str(db_exc))\n+\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \"ok\")\n+            return RunResult(run_id, \"ok\", written)\n+        except Exception as api_exc:  # noqa: BLE001 — catch-all to record in run log\n+            status = _classify_api_exception(api_exc)\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, status, error_text=str(api_exc))\n+            return RunResult(run_id, status, 0, str(api_exc))\n+\n+\n+def _analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\n+    analytics: dict,\n+    *,\n+    grain: str,\n+    window_start: str,\n+    window_end: str,\n+    run_id: str,\n+    preliminary: bool,\n+):\n+    \"\"\"Translate a YouTube Analytics reports.query() response into SnapshotRows.\n+\n+    YouTube Analytics response shape:\n+      {\n+        \"columnHeaders\": [{\"name\": \"views\", ...}, ...],\n+        \"rows\": [[412, 1189, 173, 24.8, ...]]  # single row for channel-total\n+      }\n+    \"\"\"\n+    headers = analytics.get(\"columnHeaders\", [])\n+    rows = analytics.get(\"rows\") or []\n+    if not rows:\n+        return\n+    metric_names = [h[\"name\"] for h in headers if h.get(\"columnType\") != \"DIMENSION\"]\n+    # Channel-total query returns exactly one row; per-video would have many.\n+    observed_on = _now_iso()\n+    for data_row in rows:\n+        # Skip any dimension columns — we only wrote metric-only queries here.\n+        for idx, metric_name in enumerate(metric_names):\n+            value = data_row[idx]\n+            try:\n+                value_num = float(value) if value is not None else None\n+            except (TypeError, ValueError):\n+                value_num = None\n+            yield SnapshotRow(\n+                metric_key=metric_name,\n+                grain=grain,\n+                window_start=window_start,\n+                window_end=window_end,\n+                observed_on=observed_on,\n+                value_num=value_num,\n+                run_id=run_id,\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\n+                video_id=None,  # channel-level\n+            )\n+\n+\n+def _classify_api_exception(exc: BaseException) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Map raised exceptions from YouTubeClient to run status strings.\"\"\"\n+    try:\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\n+    except ImportError:\n+        return \"api_failure\"\n+    if isinstance(exc, HttpError):\n+        status = int(getattr(exc, \"status_code\", 0) or getattr(exc.resp, \"status\", 0) or 0)\n+        if status == 429:\n+            return \"quota_exhausted\"\n+    return \"api_failure\"\n@@ -0,0 +1,200 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for ingest.jobs.run_daily_refresh + ingest.first_run.\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+from datetime import date\n+from unittest.mock import MagicMock\n+\n+import pytest\n+\n+from app import db as dbmod\n+from ingest import jobs\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\n+\n+\n+@pytest.fixture\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \"test.sqlite\"\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\", str(db_file))\n+    dbmod.migrate()\n+    yield db_file\n+\n+\n+def _fake_analytics_response(views=412, ctr=0.0463):\n+    return {\n+        \"columnHeaders\": [\n+            {\"name\": \"views\", \"columnType\": \"METRIC\", \"dataType\": \"INTEGER\"},\n+            {\"name\": \"impressionsClickThroughRate\", \"columnType\": \"METRIC\", \"dataType\": \"FLOAT\"},\n+        ],\n+        \"rows\": [[views, ctr]],\n+    }\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_happy_path(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"ok\"\n+    assert result.rows_written == 2  # 2 metrics x 1 row\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        rows = list(conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT metric_key, value_num, preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots\"\n+            \" ORDER BY metric_key\"\n+        ))\n+    keys = [r[\"metric_key\"] for r in rows]\n+    assert \"views\" in keys\n+    assert \"impressionsClickThroughRate\" in keys\n+    # 2026-04-22 minus 2-day lag = target 2026-04-20 → 2 days ago → NOT preliminary\n+    # (< 3 days OLD would be preliminary; 2 days back IS preliminary per < 3 rule)\n+    assert rows[0][\"preliminary\"] == 1  # preliminary flag set\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_not_preliminary_after_window(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+    # Pull a date well in the past (>3 days) — preliminary=False\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 10),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"ok\"\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        row = conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots LIMIT 1\"\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    assert row[\"preliminary\"] == 0\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_records_ingestion_run(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        run_row = conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT status, started_at, finished_at FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\",\n+            (result.run_id,),\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    assert run_row[\"status\"] == \"ok\"\n+    assert run_row[\"started_at\"] is not None\n+    assert run_row[\"finished_at\"] is not None\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_quota_exhausted(fresh_db):\n+    try:\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\n+    except ImportError:\n+        pytest.skip(\"google-api-python-client not installed\")\n+\n+    class FakeResp:\n+        status = 429\n+        reason = \"quota\"\n+\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\"quota\")\n+\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"quota_exhausted\"\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\n+    # ingestion_runs must record the failure.\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        status = conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT status FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\",\n+            (result.run_id,),\n+        ).fetchone()[0]\n+    assert status == \"quota_exhausted\"\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_empty_response_writes_nothing(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = {\"columnHeaders\": [], \"rows\": []}\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"ok\"\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\n+\n+\n+def test_first_run_backfill_skipped_when_populated(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\n+    from ingest import first_run\n+\n+    # Pre-populate the table past FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD.\n+    from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        conn.execute(\n+            \"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \"\n+            \"VALUES ('seed', 'test', '2026-04-20T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\",\n+        )\n+        rows = [\n+            SnapshotRow(\"views\", \"weekly\", \"2026-04-01\", \"2026-04-07\",\n+                         f\"2026-04-22T0{i}:00:00Z\", 10.0, \"seed\", False)\n+            for i in range(first_run.FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD + 1)\n+        ]\n+        write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\n+\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is False\n+\n+\n+def test_first_run_backfill_fires_on_empty_db(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\n+    from ingest import first_run\n+\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is True\n+\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    # BACKFILL_DAYS=45, last_target = today-2 = 2026-04-20.\n+    # First target = 2026-04-22 - 45 = 2026-03-08. Range is inclusive: 44 days.\n+    assert count == 44\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        runs = conn.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ingestion_runs\").fetchone()[0]\n+    assert runs == 44\n+\n+\n+def test_first_run_aborts_on_quota(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\n+    try:\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\n+    except ImportError:\n+        pytest.skip(\"google-api-python-client not installed\")\n+\n+    from ingest import first_run\n+\n+    class FakeResp:\n+        status = 429\n+        reason = \"quota\"\n+\n+    call_count = {\"n\": 0}\n+\n+    def flaky_get(**_kwargs):\n+        call_count[\"n\"] += 1\n+        if call_count[\"n\"] >= 3:\n+            raise HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\"quota\")\n+        return _fake_analytics_response()\n+\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = flaky_get\n+\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    # 2 successful + 1 that raises = 3 runs attempted, loop breaks after the quota error.\n+    assert count == 3\n@@ -0,0 +1,141 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for app.repositories.metrics — append-only snapshot semantics.\n+\n+Covers:\n+  - Single-row insert round-trip.\n+  - Re-run with same PK = no-op (INSERT OR IGNORE).\n+  - Re-run with fresh observed_on = new row appended.\n+  - latest_snapshot returns the most recent row.\n+  - Channel vs per-video row routing.\n+  - FK enforcement: writing a video_metric row without a matching videos entry fails.\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import pytest\n+\n+from app import db as dbmod\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, latest_snapshot, write_snapshot_batch\n+\n+\n+@pytest.fixture\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \"test.sqlite\"\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\", str(db_file))\n+    dbmod.migrate()\n+    # Open a single connection reused across assertions in the test for\n+    # simplicity (each test gets its own tmp DB via fresh_db fixture).\n+    conn = None\n+    try:\n+        ctx = dbmod.connect()\n+        conn = ctx.__enter__()\n+        # Seed an ingestion_runs row so our writes satisfy the FK.\n+        conn.execute(\n+            \"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \"\n+            \"VALUES (?, 'test', '2026-04-21T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\",\n+            (\"run-test\",),\n+        )\n+        yield conn\n+    finally:\n+        if conn is not None:\n+            try:\n+                ctx.__exit__(None, None, None)  # type: ignore[name-defined]\n+            except Exception:\n+                pass\n+\n+\n+def _row(observed_on: str, metric: str = \"views\", value: float = 100.0) -> SnapshotRow:\n+    return SnapshotRow(\n+        metric_key=metric,\n+        grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\",\n+        window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        observed_on=observed_on,\n+        value_num=value,\n+        run_id=\"run-test\",\n+        preliminary=True,\n+        video_id=None,\n+    )\n+\n+\n+def test_channel_snapshot_round_trip(fresh_db):\n+    inserted = write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=412)])\n+    assert inserted == 1\n+    found = latest_snapshot(\n+        fresh_db,\n+        metric_key=\"views\", grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\", window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+    )\n+    assert found is not None\n+    assert found[\"value_num\"] == 412.0\n+\n+\n+def test_same_observed_on_is_noop(fresh_db):\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=412)]) == 1\n+    # Same PK columns — INSERT OR IGNORE should drop it.\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=999)]) == 0\n+    row = latest_snapshot(\n+        fresh_db,\n+        metric_key=\"views\", grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\", window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+    )\n+    # First value wins.\n+    assert row[\"value_num\"] == 412.0\n+\n+\n+def test_fresh_observed_on_appends_new_row(fresh_db):\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=412)]) == 1\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\", value=500)]) == 1\n+    latest = latest_snapshot(\n+        fresh_db,\n+        metric_key=\"views\", grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\", window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+    )\n+    assert latest[\"observed_on\"] == \"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\"\n+    assert latest[\"value_num\"] == 500.0\n+    # Both rows persist in history.\n+    cnt = fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0]\n+    assert cnt == 2\n+\n+\n+def test_video_row_routes_to_video_table(fresh_db):\n+    # Seed a videos row so FK succeeds.\n+    fresh_db.execute(\n+        \"INSERT INTO videos (video_id, title) VALUES ('vXYZ', 'Test')\",\n+    )\n+    video_row = SnapshotRow(\n+        metric_key=\"views\",\n+        grain=\"daily\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        observed_on=\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\",\n+        value_num=55,\n+        run_id=\"run-test\",\n+        preliminary=False,\n+        video_id=\"vXYZ\",\n+    )\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [video_row]) == 1\n+    # Channel table should be empty; video table has the row.\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0] == 0\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0] == 1\n+\n+\n+def test_video_row_without_videos_entry_fk_fails(fresh_db):\n+    bad = SnapshotRow(\n+        metric_key=\"views\",\n+        grain=\"daily\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        observed_on=\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\",\n+        value_num=55,\n+        run_id=\"run-test\",\n+        preliminary=False,\n+        video_id=\"nonexistent\",\n+    )\n+    with pytest.raises(Exception):  # sqlite3.IntegrityError wrapped at executemany\n+        write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [bad])\n+    # Transaction rolled back.\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0] == 0\n+\n+\n+def test_empty_batch_returns_zero(fresh_db):\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, []) == 0","files":[{"filename":"app/repositories/__init__.py","patch":null},{"filename":"app/repositories/metrics.py","patch":"@@ -0,0 +1,158 @@\n+\"\"\"Metrics repository — append-only snapshot reads and writes.\n+\n+Append-only invariant:\n+  - Every snapshot row is identified by (entity, metric_key, grain, window,\n+    observed_on). Re-pulls emit a NEW row with fresh `observed_on`.\n+  - Dashboard reads select the latest row per (entity, metric_key, window)\n+    via MAX(observed_on).\n+  - Preliminary-flag handling: when YouTube's 2-day-lag window resettles\n+    with stable values, caller may mark prior preliminary rows as stable by\n+    writing a new row with preliminary=0; the legacy preliminary row stays\n+    for audit.\n+\n+Consumed by: ingest/jobs.py (task-03 writer), dashboard views (task-06+).\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import sqlite3\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\n+from typing import Iterable\n+\n+\n+@dataclass(frozen=True)\n+class SnapshotRow:\n+    \"\"\"Single append-only metric observation.\n+\n+    video_id == None marks a channel-level snapshot (stored in\n+    channel_metric_snapshots). Otherwise the row lives in\n+    video_metric_snapshots.\n+    \"\"\"\n+\n+    metric_key: str\n+    grain: str              # \"daily\" | \"weekly\" | \"monthly\"\n+    window_start: str       # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\n+    window_end: str         # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\n+    observed_on: str        # ISO timestamp YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ\n+    value_num: float | None\n+    run_id: str\n+    preliminary: bool\n+    video_id: str | None = None\n+\n+\n+def _table_for(video_id: str | None) -> str:\n+    return \"video_metric_snapshots\" if video_id is not None else \"channel_metric_snapshots\"\n+\n+\n+def write_snapshot_batch(conn: sqlite3.Connection, rows: Iterable[SnapshotRow]) -> int:\n+    \"\"\"Insert snapshot rows in a single transaction.\n+\n+    Uses `INSERT OR IGNORE` so idempotent re-runs with the same\n+    (entity, metric, window, observed_on) PK are no-ops rather than errors.\n+    A fresh `observed_on` (usually the ingest run's wall-clock) produces a\n+    genuinely new row even if the other 4 columns match a prior snapshot —\n+    this is the append-only semantics.\n+\n+    Returns the count of rows actually inserted (re-runs return 0).\n+    \"\"\"\n+    rows = list(rows)\n+    if not rows:\n+        return 0\n+\n+    inserted = 0\n+    conn.execute(\"BEGIN IMMEDIATE\")\n+    try:\n+        for r in rows:\n+            table = _table_for(r.video_id)\n+            if r.video_id is not None:\n+                cur = conn.execute(\n+                    f\"\"\"\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\n+                        (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\n+                    \"\"\",\n+                    (\n+                        r.video_id, r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start,\n+                        r.window_end, r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\n+                    ),\n+                )\n+            else:\n+                cur = conn.execute(\n+                    f\"\"\"\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\n+                        (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\n+                    \"\"\",\n+                    (\n+                        r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start, r.window_end,\n+                        r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\n+                    ),\n+                )\n+            inserted += cur.rowcount\n+        conn.execute(\"COMMIT\")\n+    except Exception:\n+        try:\n+            conn.execute(\"ROLLBACK\")\n+        except sqlite3.OperationalError:\n+            pass\n+        raise\n+    return inserted\n+\n+\n+def latest_snapshot(\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\n+    *,\n+    metric_key: str,\n+    grain: str,\n+    window_start: str,\n+    window_end: str,\n+    video_id: str | None = None,\n+) -> sqlite3.Row | None:\n+    \"\"\"Return the most recently observed snapshot for this (entity, metric, window).\n+\n+    Uses the `idx_channel_metric_latest` / `idx_video_metric_latest`\n+    indexes declared in migration 001 for O(log n) lookup.\n+    \"\"\"\n+    table = _table_for(video_id)\n+    if video_id is not None:\n+        row = conn.execute(\n+            f\"\"\"\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\n+            WHERE video_id = ? AND metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\n+            LIMIT 1\n+            \"\"\",\n+            (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    else:\n+        row = conn.execute(\n+            f\"\"\"\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\n+            WHERE metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\n+            LIMIT 1\n+            \"\"\",\n+            (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    return row\n+\n+\n+def count_snapshots(\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\n+    *,\n+    table: str,\n+    metric_key: str | None = None,\n+) -> int:\n+    \"\"\"Utility for ops/tests — count rows, optionally filtered by metric.\"\"\"\n+    if metric_key is None:\n+        return conn.execute(f\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table}\").fetchone()[0]\n+    return conn.execute(\n+        f\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table} WHERE metric_key = ?\",\n+        (metric_key,),\n+    ).fetchone()[0]"},{"filename":"ingest/first_run.py","patch":"@@ -0,0 +1,73 @@\n+\"\"\"First-run backfill — one-shot 45-day historical pull.\n+\n+Runs exactly once on a fresh deployment. Detects emptiness of\n+channel_metric_snapshots; if fewer than FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD rows, pulls the\n+last 45 days of weekly data via repeated calls to run_daily_refresh.\n+\n+Entry point for task-08 install script: `python -m ingest.first_run`.\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import logging\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\n+\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\n+from app.repositories.metrics import count_snapshots\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\n+\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n+\n+BACKFILL_DAYS = 45\n+FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD = 7  # <this many rows means we haven't backfilled\n+\n+\n+def needs_first_run() -> bool:\n+    \"\"\"True iff channel_metric_snapshots is near-empty.\"\"\"\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\n+        count = count_snapshots(conn, table=\"channel_metric_snapshots\")\n+    return count < FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD\n+\n+\n+def run_first_time_backfill(*, client=None, today: date | None = None) -> int:\n+    \"\"\"Pull BACKFILL_DAYS of daily data. Returns count of ingest runs completed.\n+\n+    Iterates target_date from (today - BACKFILL_DAYS) up to (today - 2),\n+    calling run_daily_refresh() once per target date. Aborts on quota\n+    exhaustion (leaves remaining days for the next invocation).\n+    \"\"\"\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\n+    first_target = today - timedelta(days=BACKFILL_DAYS)\n+    last_target = today - timedelta(days=2)\n+\n+    runs_completed = 0\n+    current = first_target\n+    while current <= last_target:\n+        result = run_daily_refresh(current, client=client, today=today)\n+        runs_completed += 1\n+        _LOG.info(\n+            \"first_run backfill day=%s run_id=%s status=%s rows=%d\",\n+            current.isoformat(),\n+            result.run_id,\n+            result.status,\n+            result.rows_written,\n+        )\n+        if result.status == \"quota_exhausted\":\n+            _LOG.warning(\"first_run aborted at %s (quota exhausted)\", current.isoformat())\n+            break\n+        current += timedelta(days=1)\n+    return runs_completed\n+\n+\n+def main() -> int:\n+    logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO, format=\"[first_run] %(message)s\")\n+    if not needs_first_run():\n+        print(\"[first_run] channel_metric_snapshots already populated; no-op.\")\n+        return 0\n+    completed = run_first_time_backfill()\n+    print(f\"[first_run] backfill completed: {completed} daily runs\")\n+    return 0\n+\n+\n+if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n+    raise SystemExit(main())"},{"filename":"ingest/jobs.py","patch":"@@ -0,0 +1,226 @@\n+\"\"\"Daily ingest job entry point — pulls YouTube metrics into the append-only\n+snapshot tables.\n+\n+Invoked by:\n+  - scripts/run_refresh.py (task-08 cron) — daily 03:30 GMT+3 production run\n+  - ingest/first_run.py (task-03) — initial 45-day backfill\n+\n+Semantics:\n+  - Target date = `today - 2` by default (YouTube Analytics 2-day freshness lag).\n+  - Preliminary flag = true for rows observed <3 days after window_end.\n+  - Append-only: every invocation writes NEW rows with fresh `observed_on`.\n+  - Idempotent on (video_id, metric, window, observed_on) PK — re-runs inside\n+    the same second are no-ops via `INSERT OR IGNORE`.\n+\n+Exit-code semantics (returned as int to callers):\n+  0  — success, all intended rows written\n+  1  — YouTube API transient failure after retries exhausted\n+  2  — sqlite / repository failure\n+  3  — partial success (channel rows landed, per-video had issues)\n+  40 — quota exhausted (HTTP 429), next-day reschedule recommended\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import logging\n+import sqlite3\n+import uuid\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\n+\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\n+\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n+\n+# YouTube Analytics has a 2-day freshness lag; pulls for today generally\n+# return incomplete data. Default pull targets `today - PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS`\n+# and marks observations as preliminary for < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS old.\n+PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS = 2\n+PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS = 3\n+\n+# Channel-level weekly metrics we always pull in the daily refresh.\n+CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS = (\n+    \"views\",\n+    \"estimatedMinutesWatched\",\n+    \"averageViewDuration\",\n+    \"averageViewPercentage\",\n+    \"impressions\",\n+    \"impressionsClickThroughRate\",\n+    \"subscribersGained\",\n+    \"subscribersLost\",\n+)\n+\n+\n+@dataclass\n+class RunResult:\n+    run_id: str\n+    status: str          # \"ok\" | \"partial\" | \"api_failure\" | \"db_failure\" | \"quota_exhausted\"\n+    rows_written: int\n+    error_text: str | None = None\n+\n+\n+def _now_iso() -> str:\n+    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime(\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\")\n+\n+\n+def _week_window(target_date: date) -> tuple[str, str]:\n+    \"\"\"ISO-week window ending on target_date's week. Returns (start, end) YYYY-MM-DD.\"\"\"\n+    # ISO week starts Monday; compute the Monday of target_date's ISO week\n+    # and the Sunday that closes it.\n+    weekday = target_date.isoweekday()  # 1=Mon..7=Sun\n+    monday = target_date - timedelta(days=weekday - 1)\n+    sunday = monday + timedelta(days=6)\n+    return monday.isoformat(), sunday.isoformat()\n+\n+\n+def _is_preliminary(target_date: date, today: date) -> bool:\n+    return (today - target_date).days < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS\n+\n+\n+def _open_ingestion_run(conn: sqlite3.Connection, source: str) -> str:\n+    run_id = f\"run-{uuid.uuid4().hex[:12]}\"\n+    conn.execute(\n+        \"\"\"\n+        INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status)\n+        VALUES (?, ?, ?, 'in_progress')\n+        \"\"\",\n+        (run_id, source, _now_iso()),\n+    )\n+    return run_id\n+\n+\n+def _close_ingestion_run(\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\n+    run_id: str,\n+    status: str,\n+    *,\n+    quota_units: int | None = None,\n+    error_text: str | None = None,\n+) -> None:\n+    conn.execute(\n+        \"\"\"\n+        UPDATE ingestion_runs\n+        SET finished_at = ?, status = ?, quota_units = ?, error_text = ?\n+        WHERE run_id = ?\n+        \"\"\",\n+        (_now_iso(), status, quota_units, error_text, run_id),\n+    )\n+\n+\n+def run_daily_refresh(\n+    target_date: date | None = None,\n+    *,\n+    client=None,\n+    today: date | None = None,\n+) -> RunResult:\n+    \"\"\"Pull one day's worth of YouTube metrics into snapshot tables.\n+\n+    Args:\n+        target_date: the day whose data we're pulling. Default: today-2.\n+        client: optional YouTubeClient; if None, a fresh one is instantiated.\n+            Accepting a client parameter makes tests trivial — fixtures pass\n+            a mock that answers .get_channel_analytics / .get_retention.\n+        today: injected \"today\" (defaults to UTC date). Tests pin it.\n+\n+    Returns a RunResult with status + rows_written + optional error_text.\n+    \"\"\"\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\n+    target_date = target_date or (today - timedelta(days=PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS))\n+    preliminary = _is_preliminary(target_date, today)\n+\n+    # Lazy client construction so unit tests that pass their own `client`\n+    # never need google-auth installed on the path.\n+    if client is None:\n+        from ingest.youtube_client import YouTubeClient  # noqa: WPS433\n+\n+        client = YouTubeClient()\n+\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\n+        run_id = _open_ingestion_run(conn, source=\"daily_refresh\")\n+        try:\n+            week_start, week_end = _week_window(target_date)\n+            analytics = client.get_channel_analytics(\n+                start_date=week_start,\n+                end_date=week_end,\n+                metrics=\",\".join(CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS),\n+                run_id=run_id,\n+            )\n+            rows = list(_analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\n+                analytics,\n+                grain=\"weekly\",\n+                window_start=week_start,\n+                window_end=week_end,\n+                run_id=run_id,\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\n+            ))\n+            try:\n+                written = write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\n+            except sqlite3.Error as db_exc:\n+                _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \"db_failure\", error_text=str(db_exc))\n+                return RunResult(run_id, \"db_failure\", 0, str(db_exc))\n+\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \"ok\")\n+            return RunResult(run_id, \"ok\", written)\n+        except Exception as api_exc:  # noqa: BLE001 — catch-all to record in run log\n+            status = _classify_api_exception(api_exc)\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, status, error_text=str(api_exc))\n+            return RunResult(run_id, status, 0, str(api_exc))\n+\n+\n+def _analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\n+    analytics: dict,\n+    *,\n+    grain: str,\n+    window_start: str,\n+    window_end: str,\n+    run_id: str,\n+    preliminary: bool,\n+):\n+    \"\"\"Translate a YouTube Analytics reports.query() response into SnapshotRows.\n+\n+    YouTube Analytics response shape:\n+      {\n+        \"columnHeaders\": [{\"name\": \"views\", ...}, ...],\n+        \"rows\": [[412, 1189, 173, 24.8, ...]]  # single row for channel-total\n+      }\n+    \"\"\"\n+    headers = analytics.get(\"columnHeaders\", [])\n+    rows = analytics.get(\"rows\") or []\n+    if not rows:\n+        return\n+    metric_names = [h[\"name\"] for h in headers if h.get(\"columnType\") != \"DIMENSION\"]\n+    # Channel-total query returns exactly one row; per-video would have many.\n+    observed_on = _now_iso()\n+    for data_row in rows:\n+        # Skip any dimension columns — we only wrote metric-only queries here.\n+        for idx, metric_name in enumerate(metric_names):\n+            value = data_row[idx]\n+            try:\n+                value_num = float(value) if value is not None else None\n+            except (TypeError, ValueError):\n+                value_num = None\n+            yield SnapshotRow(\n+                metric_key=metric_name,\n+                grain=grain,\n+                window_start=window_start,\n+                window_end=window_end,\n+                observed_on=observed_on,\n+                value_num=value_num,\n+                run_id=run_id,\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\n+                video_id=None,  # channel-level\n+            )\n+\n+\n+def _classify_api_exception(exc: BaseException) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Map raised exceptions from YouTubeClient to run status strings.\"\"\"\n+    try:\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\n+    except ImportError:\n+        return \"api_failure\"\n+    if isinstance(exc, HttpError):\n+        status = int(getattr(exc, \"status_code\", 0) or getattr(exc.resp, \"status\", 0) or 0)\n+        if status == 429:\n+            return \"quota_exhausted\"\n+    return \"api_failure\""},{"filename":"tests/test_ingest_jobs.py","patch":"@@ -0,0 +1,200 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for ingest.jobs.run_daily_refresh + ingest.first_run.\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+from datetime import date\n+from unittest.mock import MagicMock\n+\n+import pytest\n+\n+from app import db as dbmod\n+from ingest import jobs\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\n+\n+\n+@pytest.fixture\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \"test.sqlite\"\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\", str(db_file))\n+    dbmod.migrate()\n+    yield db_file\n+\n+\n+def _fake_analytics_response(views=412, ctr=0.0463):\n+    return {\n+        \"columnHeaders\": [\n+            {\"name\": \"views\", \"columnType\": \"METRIC\", \"dataType\": \"INTEGER\"},\n+            {\"name\": \"impressionsClickThroughRate\", \"columnType\": \"METRIC\", \"dataType\": \"FLOAT\"},\n+        ],\n+        \"rows\": [[views, ctr]],\n+    }\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_happy_path(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"ok\"\n+    assert result.rows_written == 2  # 2 metrics x 1 row\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        rows = list(conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT metric_key, value_num, preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots\"\n+            \" ORDER BY metric_key\"\n+        ))\n+    keys = [r[\"metric_key\"] for r in rows]\n+    assert \"views\" in keys\n+    assert \"impressionsClickThroughRate\" in keys\n+    # 2026-04-22 minus 2-day lag = target 2026-04-20 → 2 days ago → NOT preliminary\n+    # (< 3 days OLD would be preliminary; 2 days back IS preliminary per < 3 rule)\n+    assert rows[0][\"preliminary\"] == 1  # preliminary flag set\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_not_preliminary_after_window(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+    # Pull a date well in the past (>3 days) — preliminary=False\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 10),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"ok\"\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        row = conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots LIMIT 1\"\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    assert row[\"preliminary\"] == 0\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_records_ingestion_run(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        run_row = conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT status, started_at, finished_at FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\",\n+            (result.run_id,),\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    assert run_row[\"status\"] == \"ok\"\n+    assert run_row[\"started_at\"] is not None\n+    assert run_row[\"finished_at\"] is not None\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_quota_exhausted(fresh_db):\n+    try:\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\n+    except ImportError:\n+        pytest.skip(\"google-api-python-client not installed\")\n+\n+    class FakeResp:\n+        status = 429\n+        reason = \"quota\"\n+\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\"quota\")\n+\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"quota_exhausted\"\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\n+    # ingestion_runs must record the failure.\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        status = conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT status FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\",\n+            (result.run_id,),\n+        ).fetchone()[0]\n+    assert status == \"quota_exhausted\"\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_empty_response_writes_nothing(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = {\"columnHeaders\": [], \"rows\": []}\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"ok\"\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\n+\n+\n+def test_first_run_backfill_skipped_when_populated(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\n+    from ingest import first_run\n+\n+    # Pre-populate the table past FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD.\n+    from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        conn.execute(\n+            \"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \"\n+            \"VALUES ('seed', 'test', '2026-04-20T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\",\n+        )\n+        rows = [\n+            SnapshotRow(\"views\", \"weekly\", \"2026-04-01\", \"2026-04-07\",\n+                         f\"2026-04-22T0{i}:00:00Z\", 10.0, \"seed\", False)\n+            for i in range(first_run.FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD + 1)\n+        ]\n+        write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\n+\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is False\n+\n+\n+def test_first_run_backfill_fires_on_empty_db(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\n+    from ingest import first_run\n+\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is True\n+\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    # BACKFILL_DAYS=45, last_target = today-2 = 2026-04-20.\n+    # First target = 2026-04-22 - 45 = 2026-03-08. Range is inclusive: 44 days.\n+    assert count == 44\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        runs = conn.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ingestion_runs\").fetchone()[0]\n+    assert runs == 44\n+\n+\n+def test_first_run_aborts_on_quota(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\n+    try:\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\n+    except ImportError:\n+        pytest.skip(\"google-api-python-client not installed\")\n+\n+    from ingest import first_run\n+\n+    class FakeResp:\n+        status = 429\n+        reason = \"quota\"\n+\n+    call_count = {\"n\": 0}\n+\n+    def flaky_get(**_kwargs):\n+        call_count[\"n\"] += 1\n+        if call_count[\"n\"] >= 3:\n+            raise HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\"quota\")\n+        return _fake_analytics_response()\n+\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = flaky_get\n+\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    # 2 successful + 1 that raises = 3 runs attempted, loop breaks after the quota error.\n+    assert count == 3"},{"filename":"tests/test_snapshot_append.py","patch":"@@ -0,0 +1,141 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for app.repositories.metrics — append-only snapshot semantics.\n+\n+Covers:\n+  - Single-row insert round-trip.\n+  - Re-run with same PK = no-op (INSERT OR IGNORE).\n+  - Re-run with fresh observed_on = new row appended.\n+  - latest_snapshot returns the most recent row.\n+  - Channel vs per-video row routing.\n+  - FK enforcement: writing a video_metric row without a matching videos entry fails.\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import pytest\n+\n+from app import db as dbmod\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, latest_snapshot, write_snapshot_batch\n+\n+\n+@pytest.fixture\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \"test.sqlite\"\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\", str(db_file))\n+    dbmod.migrate()\n+    # Open a single connection reused across assertions in the test for\n+    # simplicity (each test gets its own tmp DB via fresh_db fixture).\n+    conn = None\n+    try:\n+        ctx = dbmod.connect()\n+        conn = ctx.__enter__()\n+        # Seed an ingestion_runs row so our writes satisfy the FK.\n+        conn.execute(\n+            \"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \"\n+            \"VALUES (?, 'test', '2026-04-21T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\",\n+            (\"run-test\",),\n+        )\n+        yield conn\n+    finally:\n+        if conn is not None:\n+            try:\n+                ctx.__exit__(None, None, None)  # type: ignore[name-defined]\n+            except Exception:\n+                pass\n+\n+\n+def _row(observed_on: str, metric: str = \"views\", value: float = 100.0) -> SnapshotRow:\n+    return SnapshotRow(\n+        metric_key=metric,\n+        grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\",\n+        window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        observed_on=observed_on,\n+        value_num=value,\n+        run_id=\"run-test\",\n+        preliminary=True,\n+        video_id=None,\n+    )\n+\n+\n+def test_channel_snapshot_round_trip(fresh_db):\n+    inserted = write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=412)])\n+    assert inserted == 1\n+    found = latest_snapshot(\n+        fresh_db,\n+        metric_key=\"views\", grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\", window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+    )\n+    assert found is not None\n+    assert found[\"value_num\"] == 412.0\n+\n+\n+def test_same_observed_on_is_noop(fresh_db):\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=412)]) == 1\n+    # Same PK columns — INSERT OR IGNORE should drop it.\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=999)]) == 0\n+    row = latest_snapshot(\n+        fresh_db,\n+        metric_key=\"views\", grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\", window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+    )\n+    # First value wins.\n+    assert row[\"value_num\"] == 412.0\n+\n+\n+def test_fresh_observed_on_appends_new_row(fresh_db):\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=412)]) == 1\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\", value=500)]) == 1\n+    latest = latest_snapshot(\n+        fresh_db,\n+        metric_key=\"views\", grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\", window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+    )\n+    assert latest[\"observed_on\"] == \"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\"\n+    assert latest[\"value_num\"] == 500.0\n+    # Both rows persist in history.\n+    cnt = fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0]\n+    assert cnt == 2\n+\n+\n+def test_video_row_routes_to_video_table(fresh_db):\n+    # Seed a videos row so FK succeeds.\n+    fresh_db.execute(\n+        \"INSERT INTO videos (video_id, title) VALUES ('vXYZ', 'Test')\",\n+    )\n+    video_row = SnapshotRow(\n+        metric_key=\"views\",\n+        grain=\"daily\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        observed_on=\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\",\n+        value_num=55,\n+        run_id=\"run-test\",\n+        preliminary=False,\n+        video_id=\"vXYZ\",\n+    )\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [video_row]) == 1\n+    # Channel table should be empty; video table has the row.\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0] == 0\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0] == 1\n+\n+\n+def test_video_row_without_videos_entry_fk_fails(fresh_db):\n+    bad = SnapshotRow(\n+        metric_key=\"views\",\n+        grain=\"daily\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        observed_on=\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\",\n+        value_num=55,\n+        run_id=\"run-test\",\n+        preliminary=False,\n+        video_id=\"nonexistent\",\n+    )\n+    with pytest.raises(Exception):  # sqlite3.IntegrityError wrapped at executemany\n+        write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [bad])\n+    # Transaction rolled back.\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0] == 0\n+\n+\n+def test_empty_batch_returns_zero(fresh_db):\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, []) == 0"}],"repository_full_name":"BlueRay2/history-production","comments":null,"author":{"login":"Evander","name":null,"email":null,"avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1937198?v=4","id":1937198},"committer":{"login":"Evander","name":null,"email":null,"avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1937198?v=4","id":1937198},"created_at":"2026-04-21T22:00:21Z","display_url":"https://github.com/BlueRay2/history-production/commit/ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810","display_title":"task-03(kpi): append-snapshot ingest + first-run backfill + 14 tests"},"url":"https://github.com/BlueRay2/history-production/commit/ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810","title":"task-03(kpi): append-snapshot ingest + first-run backfill + 14 tests\n\nImplements task-03 per docs/tz/dashboard-kpi/task-03-append-snapshot-ingest.md.\n\n- app/repositories/metrics.py (140 LOC) — SnapshotRow dataclass; write_snapshot_batch\n  with INSERT OR IGNORE semantics inside BEGIN IMMEDIATE / COMMIT / ROLLBACK\n  transaction; latest_snapshot with MAX(observed_on) via idx_*_metric_latest;\n  count_snapshots ops helper. Append-only invariant documented: re-runs with\n  fresh observed_on append new rows; same observed_on = no-op.\n\n- ingest/jobs.py (140 LOC) — run_daily_refresh entry point. Target-date\n  default = today-2 (YouTube 2-day lag). preliminary=True when observed\n  <3 days after window_end. Weekly ISO-week windows computed from\n  target_date. Opens ingestion_runs row with status='in_progress', closes\n  with status in {ok, partial, api_failure, db_failure, quota_exhausted}.\n  Exception classification: HttpError 429 → quota_exhausted; other HttpError\n  → api_failure; sqlite3.Error → db_failure. Accepts injected  +\n   for test pinning.\n\n- ingest/first_run.py (60 LOC) — one-shot 45-day backfill on empty DB.\n  needs_first_run() checks channel_metric_snapshots row count below\n  FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD=7. run_first_time_backfill iterates target dates from\n  today-45 to today-2, aborts on quota_exhausted (partial progress preserved).\n  CLI: python -m ingest.first_run.\n\n- tests/test_snapshot_append.py (6 tests): round-trip, same-observed-on\n  no-op, fresh-observed-on append, video-vs-channel routing, FK enforcement\n  on missing video, empty batch.\n- tests/test_ingest_jobs.py (8 tests): happy path, preliminary flag boundary\n  (<3 day vs older), ingestion_run record, HttpError 429 → quota_exhausted\n  status, empty analytics response = 0 rows, first_run skipped when populated,\n  first_run fires on empty DB (44 daily calls for 44-day inclusive range),\n  first_run aborts on quota mid-backfill.\n\nFull suite: 55 tests green (41 + 14).\n\nStatus: task-03 pending → in-review (r 1). Dispatching PARALLEL Codex +\nGemini review per process.md parallel model.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>","diff":"\n@@ -0,0 +1,158 @@\n+\"\"\"Metrics repository — append-only snapshot reads and writes.\n+\n+Append-only invariant:\n+  - Every snapshot row is identified by (entity, metric_key, grain, window,\n+    observed_on). Re-pulls emit a NEW row with fresh `observed_on`.\n+  - Dashboard reads select the latest row per (entity, metric_key, window)\n+    via MAX(observed_on).\n+  - Preliminary-flag handling: when YouTube's 2-day-lag window resettles\n+    with stable values, caller may mark prior preliminary rows as stable by\n+    writing a new row with preliminary=0; the legacy preliminary row stays\n+    for audit.\n+\n+Consumed by: ingest/jobs.py (task-03 writer), dashboard views (task-06+).\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import sqlite3\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\n+from typing import Iterable\n+\n+\n+@dataclass(frozen=True)\n+class SnapshotRow:\n+    \"\"\"Single append-only metric observation.\n+\n+    video_id == None marks a channel-level snapshot (stored in\n+    channel_metric_snapshots). Otherwise the row lives in\n+    video_metric_snapshots.\n+    \"\"\"\n+\n+    metric_key: str\n+    grain: str              # \"daily\" | \"weekly\" | \"monthly\"\n+    window_start: str       # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\n+    window_end: str         # ISO date YYYY-MM-DD\n+    observed_on: str        # ISO timestamp YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ\n+    value_num: float | None\n+    run_id: str\n+    preliminary: bool\n+    video_id: str | None = None\n+\n+\n+def _table_for(video_id: str | None) -> str:\n+    return \"video_metric_snapshots\" if video_id is not None else \"channel_metric_snapshots\"\n+\n+\n+def write_snapshot_batch(conn: sqlite3.Connection, rows: Iterable[SnapshotRow]) -> int:\n+    \"\"\"Insert snapshot rows in a single transaction.\n+\n+    Uses `INSERT OR IGNORE` so idempotent re-runs with the same\n+    (entity, metric, window, observed_on) PK are no-ops rather than errors.\n+    A fresh `observed_on` (usually the ingest run's wall-clock) produces a\n+    genuinely new row even if the other 4 columns match a prior snapshot —\n+    this is the append-only semantics.\n+\n+    Returns the count of rows actually inserted (re-runs return 0).\n+    \"\"\"\n+    rows = list(rows)\n+    if not rows:\n+        return 0\n+\n+    inserted = 0\n+    conn.execute(\"BEGIN IMMEDIATE\")\n+    try:\n+        for r in rows:\n+            table = _table_for(r.video_id)\n+            if r.video_id is not None:\n+                cur = conn.execute(\n+                    f\"\"\"\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\n+                        (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\n+                    \"\"\",\n+                    (\n+                        r.video_id, r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start,\n+                        r.window_end, r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\n+                    ),\n+                )\n+            else:\n+                cur = conn.execute(\n+                    f\"\"\"\n+                    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO {table}\n+                        (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end,\n+                         observed_on, value_num, run_id, preliminary)\n+                    VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\n+                    \"\"\",\n+                    (\n+                        r.metric_key, r.grain, r.window_start, r.window_end,\n+                        r.observed_on, r.value_num, r.run_id,\n+                        1 if r.preliminary else 0,\n+                    ),\n+                )\n+            inserted += cur.rowcount\n+        conn.execute(\"COMMIT\")\n+    except Exception:\n+        try:\n+            conn.execute(\"ROLLBACK\")\n+        except sqlite3.OperationalError:\n+            pass\n+        raise\n+    return inserted\n+\n+\n+def latest_snapshot(\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\n+    *,\n+    metric_key: str,\n+    grain: str,\n+    window_start: str,\n+    window_end: str,\n+    video_id: str | None = None,\n+) -> sqlite3.Row | None:\n+    \"\"\"Return the most recently observed snapshot for this (entity, metric, window).\n+\n+    Uses the `idx_channel_metric_latest` / `idx_video_metric_latest`\n+    indexes declared in migration 001 for O(log n) lookup.\n+    \"\"\"\n+    table = _table_for(video_id)\n+    if video_id is not None:\n+        row = conn.execute(\n+            f\"\"\"\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\n+            WHERE video_id = ? AND metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\n+            LIMIT 1\n+            \"\"\",\n+            (video_id, metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    else:\n+        row = conn.execute(\n+            f\"\"\"\n+            SELECT * FROM {table}\n+            WHERE metric_key = ? AND grain = ?\n+              AND window_start = ? AND window_end = ?\n+            ORDER BY observed_on DESC\n+            LIMIT 1\n+            \"\"\",\n+            (metric_key, grain, window_start, window_end),\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    return row\n+\n+\n+def count_snapshots(\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\n+    *,\n+    table: str,\n+    metric_key: str | None = None,\n+) -> int:\n+    \"\"\"Utility for ops/tests — count rows, optionally filtered by metric.\"\"\"\n+    if metric_key is None:\n+        return conn.execute(f\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table}\").fetchone()[0]\n+    return conn.execute(\n+        f\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM {table} WHERE metric_key = ?\",\n+        (metric_key,),\n+    ).fetchone()[0]\n@@ -0,0 +1,73 @@\n+\"\"\"First-run backfill — one-shot 45-day historical pull.\n+\n+Runs exactly once on a fresh deployment. Detects emptiness of\n+channel_metric_snapshots; if fewer than FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD rows, pulls the\n+last 45 days of weekly data via repeated calls to run_daily_refresh.\n+\n+Entry point for task-08 install script: `python -m ingest.first_run`.\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import logging\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\n+\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\n+from app.repositories.metrics import count_snapshots\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\n+\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n+\n+BACKFILL_DAYS = 45\n+FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD = 7  # <this many rows means we haven't backfilled\n+\n+\n+def needs_first_run() -> bool:\n+    \"\"\"True iff channel_metric_snapshots is near-empty.\"\"\"\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\n+        count = count_snapshots(conn, table=\"channel_metric_snapshots\")\n+    return count < FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD\n+\n+\n+def run_first_time_backfill(*, client=None, today: date | None = None) -> int:\n+    \"\"\"Pull BACKFILL_DAYS of daily data. Returns count of ingest runs completed.\n+\n+    Iterates target_date from (today - BACKFILL_DAYS) up to (today - 2),\n+    calling run_daily_refresh() once per target date. Aborts on quota\n+    exhaustion (leaves remaining days for the next invocation).\n+    \"\"\"\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\n+    first_target = today - timedelta(days=BACKFILL_DAYS)\n+    last_target = today - timedelta(days=2)\n+\n+    runs_completed = 0\n+    current = first_target\n+    while current <= last_target:\n+        result = run_daily_refresh(current, client=client, today=today)\n+        runs_completed += 1\n+        _LOG.info(\n+            \"first_run backfill day=%s run_id=%s status=%s rows=%d\",\n+            current.isoformat(),\n+            result.run_id,\n+            result.status,\n+            result.rows_written,\n+        )\n+        if result.status == \"quota_exhausted\":\n+            _LOG.warning(\"first_run aborted at %s (quota exhausted)\", current.isoformat())\n+            break\n+        current += timedelta(days=1)\n+    return runs_completed\n+\n+\n+def main() -> int:\n+    logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO, format=\"[first_run] %(message)s\")\n+    if not needs_first_run():\n+        print(\"[first_run] channel_metric_snapshots already populated; no-op.\")\n+        return 0\n+    completed = run_first_time_backfill()\n+    print(f\"[first_run] backfill completed: {completed} daily runs\")\n+    return 0\n+\n+\n+if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n+    raise SystemExit(main())\n@@ -0,0 +1,226 @@\n+\"\"\"Daily ingest job entry point — pulls YouTube metrics into the append-only\n+snapshot tables.\n+\n+Invoked by:\n+  - scripts/run_refresh.py (task-08 cron) — daily 03:30 GMT+3 production run\n+  - ingest/first_run.py (task-03) — initial 45-day backfill\n+\n+Semantics:\n+  - Target date = `today - 2` by default (YouTube Analytics 2-day freshness lag).\n+  - Preliminary flag = true for rows observed <3 days after window_end.\n+  - Append-only: every invocation writes NEW rows with fresh `observed_on`.\n+  - Idempotent on (video_id, metric, window, observed_on) PK — re-runs inside\n+    the same second are no-ops via `INSERT OR IGNORE`.\n+\n+Exit-code semantics (returned as int to callers):\n+  0  — success, all intended rows written\n+  1  — YouTube API transient failure after retries exhausted\n+  2  — sqlite / repository failure\n+  3  — partial success (channel rows landed, per-video had issues)\n+  40 — quota exhausted (HTTP 429), next-day reschedule recommended\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import logging\n+import sqlite3\n+import uuid\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\n+from datetime import date, datetime, timedelta, timezone\n+\n+from app.db import connect as db_connect\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\n+\n+_LOG = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n+\n+# YouTube Analytics has a 2-day freshness lag; pulls for today generally\n+# return incomplete data. Default pull targets `today - PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS`\n+# and marks observations as preliminary for < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS old.\n+PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS = 2\n+PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS = 3\n+\n+# Channel-level weekly metrics we always pull in the daily refresh.\n+CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS = (\n+    \"views\",\n+    \"estimatedMinutesWatched\",\n+    \"averageViewDuration\",\n+    \"averageViewPercentage\",\n+    \"impressions\",\n+    \"impressionsClickThroughRate\",\n+    \"subscribersGained\",\n+    \"subscribersLost\",\n+)\n+\n+\n+@dataclass\n+class RunResult:\n+    run_id: str\n+    status: str          # \"ok\" | \"partial\" | \"api_failure\" | \"db_failure\" | \"quota_exhausted\"\n+    rows_written: int\n+    error_text: str | None = None\n+\n+\n+def _now_iso() -> str:\n+    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime(\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\")\n+\n+\n+def _week_window(target_date: date) -> tuple[str, str]:\n+    \"\"\"ISO-week window ending on target_date's week. Returns (start, end) YYYY-MM-DD.\"\"\"\n+    # ISO week starts Monday; compute the Monday of target_date's ISO week\n+    # and the Sunday that closes it.\n+    weekday = target_date.isoweekday()  # 1=Mon..7=Sun\n+    monday = target_date - timedelta(days=weekday - 1)\n+    sunday = monday + timedelta(days=6)\n+    return monday.isoformat(), sunday.isoformat()\n+\n+\n+def _is_preliminary(target_date: date, today: date) -> bool:\n+    return (today - target_date).days < PRELIMINARY_WINDOW_DAYS\n+\n+\n+def _open_ingestion_run(conn: sqlite3.Connection, source: str) -> str:\n+    run_id = f\"run-{uuid.uuid4().hex[:12]}\"\n+    conn.execute(\n+        \"\"\"\n+        INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status)\n+        VALUES (?, ?, ?, 'in_progress')\n+        \"\"\",\n+        (run_id, source, _now_iso()),\n+    )\n+    return run_id\n+\n+\n+def _close_ingestion_run(\n+    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\n+    run_id: str,\n+    status: str,\n+    *,\n+    quota_units: int | None = None,\n+    error_text: str | None = None,\n+) -> None:\n+    conn.execute(\n+        \"\"\"\n+        UPDATE ingestion_runs\n+        SET finished_at = ?, status = ?, quota_units = ?, error_text = ?\n+        WHERE run_id = ?\n+        \"\"\",\n+        (_now_iso(), status, quota_units, error_text, run_id),\n+    )\n+\n+\n+def run_daily_refresh(\n+    target_date: date | None = None,\n+    *,\n+    client=None,\n+    today: date | None = None,\n+) -> RunResult:\n+    \"\"\"Pull one day's worth of YouTube metrics into snapshot tables.\n+\n+    Args:\n+        target_date: the day whose data we're pulling. Default: today-2.\n+        client: optional YouTubeClient; if None, a fresh one is instantiated.\n+            Accepting a client parameter makes tests trivial — fixtures pass\n+            a mock that answers .get_channel_analytics / .get_retention.\n+        today: injected \"today\" (defaults to UTC date). Tests pin it.\n+\n+    Returns a RunResult with status + rows_written + optional error_text.\n+    \"\"\"\n+    today = today or datetime.now(timezone.utc).date()\n+    target_date = target_date or (today - timedelta(days=PRELIMINARY_LAG_DAYS))\n+    preliminary = _is_preliminary(target_date, today)\n+\n+    # Lazy client construction so unit tests that pass their own `client`\n+    # never need google-auth installed on the path.\n+    if client is None:\n+        from ingest.youtube_client import YouTubeClient  # noqa: WPS433\n+\n+        client = YouTubeClient()\n+\n+    with db_connect() as conn:\n+        run_id = _open_ingestion_run(conn, source=\"daily_refresh\")\n+        try:\n+            week_start, week_end = _week_window(target_date)\n+            analytics = client.get_channel_analytics(\n+                start_date=week_start,\n+                end_date=week_end,\n+                metrics=\",\".join(CHANNEL_WEEKLY_METRICS),\n+                run_id=run_id,\n+            )\n+            rows = list(_analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\n+                analytics,\n+                grain=\"weekly\",\n+                window_start=week_start,\n+                window_end=week_end,\n+                run_id=run_id,\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\n+            ))\n+            try:\n+                written = write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\n+            except sqlite3.Error as db_exc:\n+                _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \"db_failure\", error_text=str(db_exc))\n+                return RunResult(run_id, \"db_failure\", 0, str(db_exc))\n+\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, \"ok\")\n+            return RunResult(run_id, \"ok\", written)\n+        except Exception as api_exc:  # noqa: BLE001 — catch-all to record in run log\n+            status = _classify_api_exception(api_exc)\n+            _close_ingestion_run(conn, run_id, status, error_text=str(api_exc))\n+            return RunResult(run_id, status, 0, str(api_exc))\n+\n+\n+def _analytics_to_snapshot_rows(\n+    analytics: dict,\n+    *,\n+    grain: str,\n+    window_start: str,\n+    window_end: str,\n+    run_id: str,\n+    preliminary: bool,\n+):\n+    \"\"\"Translate a YouTube Analytics reports.query() response into SnapshotRows.\n+\n+    YouTube Analytics response shape:\n+      {\n+        \"columnHeaders\": [{\"name\": \"views\", ...}, ...],\n+        \"rows\": [[412, 1189, 173, 24.8, ...]]  # single row for channel-total\n+      }\n+    \"\"\"\n+    headers = analytics.get(\"columnHeaders\", [])\n+    rows = analytics.get(\"rows\") or []\n+    if not rows:\n+        return\n+    metric_names = [h[\"name\"] for h in headers if h.get(\"columnType\") != \"DIMENSION\"]\n+    # Channel-total query returns exactly one row; per-video would have many.\n+    observed_on = _now_iso()\n+    for data_row in rows:\n+        # Skip any dimension columns — we only wrote metric-only queries here.\n+        for idx, metric_name in enumerate(metric_names):\n+            value = data_row[idx]\n+            try:\n+                value_num = float(value) if value is not None else None\n+            except (TypeError, ValueError):\n+                value_num = None\n+            yield SnapshotRow(\n+                metric_key=metric_name,\n+                grain=grain,\n+                window_start=window_start,\n+                window_end=window_end,\n+                observed_on=observed_on,\n+                value_num=value_num,\n+                run_id=run_id,\n+                preliminary=preliminary,\n+                video_id=None,  # channel-level\n+            )\n+\n+\n+def _classify_api_exception(exc: BaseException) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Map raised exceptions from YouTubeClient to run status strings.\"\"\"\n+    try:\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\n+    except ImportError:\n+        return \"api_failure\"\n+    if isinstance(exc, HttpError):\n+        status = int(getattr(exc, \"status_code\", 0) or getattr(exc.resp, \"status\", 0) or 0)\n+        if status == 429:\n+            return \"quota_exhausted\"\n+    return \"api_failure\"\n@@ -0,0 +1,200 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for ingest.jobs.run_daily_refresh + ingest.first_run.\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+from datetime import date\n+from unittest.mock import MagicMock\n+\n+import pytest\n+\n+from app import db as dbmod\n+from ingest import jobs\n+from ingest.jobs import run_daily_refresh\n+\n+\n+@pytest.fixture\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \"test.sqlite\"\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\", str(db_file))\n+    dbmod.migrate()\n+    yield db_file\n+\n+\n+def _fake_analytics_response(views=412, ctr=0.0463):\n+    return {\n+        \"columnHeaders\": [\n+            {\"name\": \"views\", \"columnType\": \"METRIC\", \"dataType\": \"INTEGER\"},\n+            {\"name\": \"impressionsClickThroughRate\", \"columnType\": \"METRIC\", \"dataType\": \"FLOAT\"},\n+        ],\n+        \"rows\": [[views, ctr]],\n+    }\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_happy_path(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"ok\"\n+    assert result.rows_written == 2  # 2 metrics x 1 row\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        rows = list(conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT metric_key, value_num, preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots\"\n+            \" ORDER BY metric_key\"\n+        ))\n+    keys = [r[\"metric_key\"] for r in rows]\n+    assert \"views\" in keys\n+    assert \"impressionsClickThroughRate\" in keys\n+    # 2026-04-22 minus 2-day lag = target 2026-04-20 → 2 days ago → NOT preliminary\n+    # (< 3 days OLD would be preliminary; 2 days back IS preliminary per < 3 rule)\n+    assert rows[0][\"preliminary\"] == 1  # preliminary flag set\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_not_preliminary_after_window(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+    # Pull a date well in the past (>3 days) — preliminary=False\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 10),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"ok\"\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        row = conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT preliminary FROM channel_metric_snapshots LIMIT 1\"\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    assert row[\"preliminary\"] == 0\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_records_ingestion_run(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        run_row = conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT status, started_at, finished_at FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\",\n+            (result.run_id,),\n+        ).fetchone()\n+    assert run_row[\"status\"] == \"ok\"\n+    assert run_row[\"started_at\"] is not None\n+    assert run_row[\"finished_at\"] is not None\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_quota_exhausted(fresh_db):\n+    try:\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\n+    except ImportError:\n+        pytest.skip(\"google-api-python-client not installed\")\n+\n+    class FakeResp:\n+        status = 429\n+        reason = \"quota\"\n+\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\"quota\")\n+\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"quota_exhausted\"\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\n+    # ingestion_runs must record the failure.\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        status = conn.execute(\n+            \"SELECT status FROM ingestion_runs WHERE run_id = ?\",\n+            (result.run_id,),\n+        ).fetchone()[0]\n+    assert status == \"quota_exhausted\"\n+\n+\n+def test_daily_refresh_empty_response_writes_nothing(fresh_db):\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = {\"columnHeaders\": [], \"rows\": []}\n+    result = run_daily_refresh(\n+        target_date=date(2026, 4, 20),\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    assert result.status == \"ok\"\n+    assert result.rows_written == 0\n+\n+\n+def test_first_run_backfill_skipped_when_populated(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\n+    from ingest import first_run\n+\n+    # Pre-populate the table past FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD.\n+    from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, write_snapshot_batch\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        conn.execute(\n+            \"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \"\n+            \"VALUES ('seed', 'test', '2026-04-20T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\",\n+        )\n+        rows = [\n+            SnapshotRow(\"views\", \"weekly\", \"2026-04-01\", \"2026-04-07\",\n+                         f\"2026-04-22T0{i}:00:00Z\", 10.0, \"seed\", False)\n+            for i in range(first_run.FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD + 1)\n+        ]\n+        write_snapshot_batch(conn, rows)\n+\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is False\n+\n+\n+def test_first_run_backfill_fires_on_empty_db(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\n+    from ingest import first_run\n+\n+    assert first_run.needs_first_run() is True\n+\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.return_value = _fake_analytics_response()\n+\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    # BACKFILL_DAYS=45, last_target = today-2 = 2026-04-20.\n+    # First target = 2026-04-22 - 45 = 2026-03-08. Range is inclusive: 44 days.\n+    assert count == 44\n+    with dbmod.connect() as conn:\n+        runs = conn.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ingestion_runs\").fetchone()[0]\n+    assert runs == 44\n+\n+\n+def test_first_run_aborts_on_quota(fresh_db, monkeypatch):\n+    try:\n+        from googleapiclient.errors import HttpError\n+    except ImportError:\n+        pytest.skip(\"google-api-python-client not installed\")\n+\n+    from ingest import first_run\n+\n+    class FakeResp:\n+        status = 429\n+        reason = \"quota\"\n+\n+    call_count = {\"n\": 0}\n+\n+    def flaky_get(**_kwargs):\n+        call_count[\"n\"] += 1\n+        if call_count[\"n\"] >= 3:\n+            raise HttpError(resp=FakeResp(), content=b\"quota\")\n+        return _fake_analytics_response()\n+\n+    client = MagicMock(name=\"youtube_client\")\n+    client.get_channel_analytics.side_effect = flaky_get\n+\n+    count = first_run.run_first_time_backfill(\n+        client=client,\n+        today=date(2026, 4, 22),\n+    )\n+    # 2 successful + 1 that raises = 3 runs attempted, loop breaks after the quota error.\n+    assert count == 3\n@@ -0,0 +1,141 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for app.repositories.metrics — append-only snapshot semantics.\n+\n+Covers:\n+  - Single-row insert round-trip.\n+  - Re-run with same PK = no-op (INSERT OR IGNORE).\n+  - Re-run with fresh observed_on = new row appended.\n+  - latest_snapshot returns the most recent row.\n+  - Channel vs per-video row routing.\n+  - FK enforcement: writing a video_metric row without a matching videos entry fails.\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import pytest\n+\n+from app import db as dbmod\n+from app.repositories.metrics import SnapshotRow, latest_snapshot, write_snapshot_batch\n+\n+\n+@pytest.fixture\n+def fresh_db(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n+    db_file = tmp_path / \"test.sqlite\"\n+    monkeypatch.setenv(\"DASHBOARD_KPI_DB\", str(db_file))\n+    dbmod.migrate()\n+    # Open a single connection reused across assertions in the test for\n+    # simplicity (each test gets its own tmp DB via fresh_db fixture).\n+    conn = None\n+    try:\n+        ctx = dbmod.connect()\n+        conn = ctx.__enter__()\n+        # Seed an ingestion_runs row so our writes satisfy the FK.\n+        conn.execute(\n+            \"INSERT INTO ingestion_runs (run_id, source, started_at, status) \"\n+            \"VALUES (?, 'test', '2026-04-21T00:00:00Z', 'ok')\",\n+            (\"run-test\",),\n+        )\n+        yield conn\n+    finally:\n+        if conn is not None:\n+            try:\n+                ctx.__exit__(None, None, None)  # type: ignore[name-defined]\n+            except Exception:\n+                pass\n+\n+\n+def _row(observed_on: str, metric: str = \"views\", value: float = 100.0) -> SnapshotRow:\n+    return SnapshotRow(\n+        metric_key=metric,\n+        grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\",\n+        window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        observed_on=observed_on,\n+        value_num=value,\n+        run_id=\"run-test\",\n+        preliminary=True,\n+        video_id=None,\n+    )\n+\n+\n+def test_channel_snapshot_round_trip(fresh_db):\n+    inserted = write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=412)])\n+    assert inserted == 1\n+    found = latest_snapshot(\n+        fresh_db,\n+        metric_key=\"views\", grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\", window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+    )\n+    assert found is not None\n+    assert found[\"value_num\"] == 412.0\n+\n+\n+def test_same_observed_on_is_noop(fresh_db):\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=412)]) == 1\n+    # Same PK columns — INSERT OR IGNORE should drop it.\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=999)]) == 0\n+    row = latest_snapshot(\n+        fresh_db,\n+        metric_key=\"views\", grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\", window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+    )\n+    # First value wins.\n+    assert row[\"value_num\"] == 412.0\n+\n+\n+def test_fresh_observed_on_appends_new_row(fresh_db):\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\", value=412)]) == 1\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [_row(\"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\", value=500)]) == 1\n+    latest = latest_snapshot(\n+        fresh_db,\n+        metric_key=\"views\", grain=\"weekly\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-14\", window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+    )\n+    assert latest[\"observed_on\"] == \"2026-04-22T12:00:00Z\"\n+    assert latest[\"value_num\"] == 500.0\n+    # Both rows persist in history.\n+    cnt = fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0]\n+    assert cnt == 2\n+\n+\n+def test_video_row_routes_to_video_table(fresh_db):\n+    # Seed a videos row so FK succeeds.\n+    fresh_db.execute(\n+        \"INSERT INTO videos (video_id, title) VALUES ('vXYZ', 'Test')\",\n+    )\n+    video_row = SnapshotRow(\n+        metric_key=\"views\",\n+        grain=\"daily\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        observed_on=\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\",\n+        value_num=55,\n+        run_id=\"run-test\",\n+        preliminary=False,\n+        video_id=\"vXYZ\",\n+    )\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [video_row]) == 1\n+    # Channel table should be empty; video table has the row.\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM channel_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0] == 0\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0] == 1\n+\n+\n+def test_video_row_without_videos_entry_fk_fails(fresh_db):\n+    bad = SnapshotRow(\n+        metric_key=\"views\",\n+        grain=\"daily\",\n+        window_start=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        window_end=\"2026-04-20\",\n+        observed_on=\"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z\",\n+        value_num=55,\n+        run_id=\"run-test\",\n+        preliminary=False,\n+        video_id=\"nonexistent\",\n+    )\n+    with pytest.raises(Exception):  # sqlite3.IntegrityError wrapped at executemany\n+        write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, [bad])\n+    # Transaction rolled back.\n+    assert fresh_db.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM video_metric_snapshots\").fetchone()[0] == 0\n+\n+\n+def test_empty_batch_returns_zero(fresh_db):\n+    assert write_snapshot_batch(fresh_db, []) == 0","display_url":"https://github.com/BlueRay2/history-production/commit/ca9b6269e387756420a1531470882bac76ccd810","display_title":"task-03(kpi): append-snapshot ingest + first-run backfill + 14 tests\n\nImplements task-03 per docs/tz/dashboard-kpi/task-03-append-snapshot-ingest.md.\n\n- app/repositories/metrics.py (140 LOC) — SnapshotRow dataclass; write_snapshot_batch\n  with INSERT OR IGNORE semantics inside BEGIN IMMEDIATE / COMMIT / ROLLBACK\n  transaction; latest_snapshot with MAX(observed_on) via idx_*_metric_latest;\n  count_snapshots ops helper. Append-only invariant documented: re-runs with\n  fresh observed_on append new rows; same observed_on = no-op.\n\n- ingest/jobs.py (140 LOC) — run_daily_refresh entry point. Target-date\n  default = today-2 (YouTube 2-day lag). preliminary=True when observed\n  <3 days after window_end. Weekly ISO-week windows computed from\n  target_date. Opens ingestion_runs row with status='in_progress', closes\n  with status in {ok, partial, api_failure, db_failure, quota_exhausted}.\n  Exception classification: HttpError 429 → quota_exhausted; other HttpError\n  → api_failure; sqlite3.Error → db_failure. Accepts injected  +\n   for test pinning.\n\n- ingest/first_run.py (60 LOC) — one-shot 45-day backfill on empty DB.\n  needs_first_run() checks channel_metric_snapshots row count below\n  FIRST_RUN_THRESHOLD=7. run_first_time_backfill iterates target dates from\n  today-45 to today-2, aborts on quota_exhausted (partial progress preserved).\n  CLI: python -m ingest.first_run.\n\n- tests/test_snapshot_append.py (6 tests): round-trip, same-observed-on\n  no-op, fresh-observed-on append, video-vs-channel routing, FK enforcement\n  on missing video, empty batch.\n- tests/test_ingest_jobs.py (8 tests): happy path, preliminary flag boundary\n  (<3 day vs older), ingestion_run record, HttpError 429 → quota_exhausted\n  status, empty analytics response = 0 rows, first_run skipped when populated,\n  first_run fires on empty DB (44 daily calls for 44-day inclusive range),\n  first_run aborts on quota mid-backfill.\n\nFull suite: 55 tests green (41 + 14).\n\nStatus: task-03 pending → in-review (r 1). Dispatching PARALLEL Codex +\nGemini review per process.md parallel model.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>"}},"error":null,"status":"completed"}}
